        "originalText": "Enter the number of shares being repurchased, whether or not the repurchase represents a sale of shares, and if applicable, whether or not the repurchased shares should return to the equity incentive plan.<br> <img height=\"156\" src=\"carta/public/11/images/4474439330649701058_TysF4TbyoWWW7IzhFK9ZOJZBxmVvrXV995E9dUMyvWhJhWt_bQ-9P_0tR5JaddbXtoNCgoJo5IijMs5G08CtGUssfMoYhYZyQCjTIGPygIllKTYHDRsYmBo8DayQUzyu7QHEweh5\" style=\"margin-left: 0px;margin-top: 0px;\" width=\"431\"><br> NOTE:  Unvested and vested shares should be repurchased separately. If repurchasing unvested shares, the stakeholder will need to first be terminated in the Stakeholders page which is explained <a href=\"https://support.carta.com/s/article/terminate-stakeholders-update\" style=\"text-decoration: none;\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>. Carta needs to track sale information for transactional reporting, disposition reporting, etc. Reflecting a company buyback is an example of a situation where a repurchase could represent a sale of shares.  <br> &nbsp;",
