    "text": {
      "text": "Authorized shares are the maximum amount of shares a company is legally allowed to issue to shareholders and is laid out in their articles of incorporation. A company decides this number themselves upon incorporation, but can increase this number by amending their corporate charter. Where can you find the authorized share count in Carta?",
