    "id": "-3766040203995158588",
    "text": {
      "text": "Outstanding shares are the total amount of shares issued out of the authorized amount. These are the total number of shares that are currently held by your shareholders. If a company issued options to an employee (i.e. the right to purchase shares at a later date), those shares would be outstanding under theShares outstanding under EIP section and can become outstanding shares once exercised. Where can you find the outstanding shares count in Carta?",
      "originalText": "Outstanding shares are the total amount of shares issued out of the authorized amount. These are the total number of shares that are currently held by your shareholders. If a company issued options to an employee (i.e. the right to purchase shares at a later date), those shares would be outstanding under the Shares outstanding under EIP section and can become outstanding shares once exercised.<br>Where can you find the outstanding&nbsp;shares count in Carta?<br>&nbsp;"
