        "originalText": "After selecting a stakeholder from the stakeholder search panel, detailed information about the selected  is separated into five primary points of interest.<br> <img height=\"744\" src=\"carta/public/11/images/6992015508507762192_Wly5jXEiKogjKV3HfXUMWH_lwEHym4dxAEQ2gCveo5RCNSrJJRWGEK0yqDgqMptm5Lz8ioemWNgA0AKYZYCSxTb0nsHpvWg5mdws3FKPkZx5eW0IdwGT-la2itrvUO5nWl3N1IbU\" width=\"530\"><br> &nbsp;  Employee information: Employee identification information will display at the top of the screen, including employee name, email address, and their current relationship with the company.<br> <img height=\"108\" src=\"carta/public/11/images/6314002720440028198_cGCX5wKnm2WGH7ydodvYKB1ROLYEcBrD2lmXp1Jeg8iOuSEx4dzFTHSH3VuyqNkodLjSA4lTzLtspv2u-StbywBa0_OGhH2tynlMKwpI7kpcOknUL02WKVFJ09Dst5e0s3Jq6edI\" width=\"212\"><br> &nbsp; ISO value chart: The ISO value chart provides a visualization for how the selected stakeholder’s ISO and ISO/NSO split grants each contribute to the annual 100K limit for exercisable ISO shares. Hover over a bar for a given year to see how the stakeholder’s individual option grants contribute to the year’s 100K limit.<br> <img height=\"198\" src=\"carta/public/11/images/1282863711055318134_c0czkcOBTWkvkY2cw-KeIq8lR-Dof1Gc63u9U5MA928ISWTYGGWxOqix_6Fw8N4Hihvw1pMJQGGfZs5oaUoHp39uSe_c61AMwG2l_3J36ngWEpq8urX3pFMcV1XpoObVQv4Xw_Ll\" width=\"432\"><br> &nbsp; <a href=\"https://support.carta.com/s/article/iso-100k-dashboard#iso-100k-report\"><b>ISO 100K report</b></a>: The ISO 100K report is a per-stakeholder report that provides a tranche-level breakdown of ISO and NSO share quantities and dollar values for all of the stakeholder’s ISO/NSO split option grants in Carta. The primary purpose of this report is to help companies and their legal counsel with ISO 100K calculations for stakeholders that are manually managed by the company.<br> The next section will break down the report further.<br> <img height=\"85\" src=\"carta/public/11/images/698344