  },
  "linked": [{
    "id": "-4828677225646872436",
    "text": {
      "text": "When first accessing the grant editor, read the informational modal (the exact text shown below is subject to change): carta/public/11/images/1989133488451092775_9R_IRhXXp6Qz_nBSh1GNMDKHD0X9evqoOVA_TZ38syyC9Cigs2xVoF8Skc1JUPU11Au2e_lNH68pySXAHpO3l4HbLbQlIzloiatIvJtUokdyIgG9Jh-aot1w7PITYUL3FWeTiDH8",
      "originalText": "When first accessing the grant editor, read the informational modal (the exact text shown below is subject to change):<br><img height=\"309\" src=\"carta/public/11/images/1989133488451092775_9R_IRhXXp6Qz_nBSh1GNMDKHD0X9evqoOVA_TZ38syyC9Cigs2xVoF8Skc1JUPU11Au2e_lNH68pySXAHpO3l4HbLbQlIzloiatIvJtUokdyIgG9Jh-aot1w7PITYUL3FWeTiDH8\" width=\"438\">",
      "associatedImage": {
        "url": "carta/public/11/images/1989133488451092775_9R_IRhXXp6Qz_nBSh1GNMDKHD0X9evqoOVA_TZ38syyC9Cigs2xVoF8Skc1JUPU11Au2e_lNH68pySXAHpO3l4HbLbQlIzloiatIvJtUokdyIgG9Jh-aot1w7PITYUL3FWeTiDH8"
      }
    }
  }, {
    "id": "-3890369005763079455",
    "text": {
      "text": "If an issuer and their legal/tax teams disagree with the ISO/NSO split values estimated by Carta’s calculator and determine that the use of the grant editor is necessary, then it’s important to recognize that by using the grant editor, you’re effectively telling Carta’s automatic calculator that it’s wrong. If this is the case, the calculator will be wrong for the stakeholder in question when evaluating their ISO option grants for potential bifurcation per the ISO 100K limit.  NOTE: Because the 100K limit is applied per stakeholder across all of their respective ISO and ISO/NSO split option grants and because Carta’s calculator will never be correct after overriding its estimate, using the grant editor on a stakeholder’s grant(s) will require that the company manually manage the ISO 100K calculation for this stakeholder from the point of override forward.",
      "originalText": "If an issuer and their legal/tax teams disagree with the ISO/NSO split values estimated by Carta’s calculator and determine that the use of the grant editor is necessary, then it’s important to recognize that by using the grant editor, you’re effectively telling Carta’s automatic calculator that it’s wrong. If this is the case, the calculator will be wrong for the stakeholder in question when evaluating their ISO option grants for potential bifurcation per the ISO 100K limit.<br><br>NOTE: Because the 100K limit is applied per stakeholder across all of their respective ISO and ISO/NSO split option grants and because Carta’s calculator will never be correct after overriding its estimate, using the grant editor on a stakeholder’s grant(s) will require that the company manually manage the ISO 100K calculation for this stakeholder from the point of override forward."
    }
  }, {
    "id": "-7483010694363351440",
    "text": {
      "text": "As an example, consider a situation in which Acme Co and their legal counsel have deemed it necessary to override Carta’s ISO/NSO split estimate via the grant editor for one of Jean Smith’s option grants. The issuing company is in this position:",
      "originalText": "As an example, consider a situation in which Acme Co and their legal counsel have deemed it necessary to override Carta’s ISO/NSO split estimate via the grant editor for one of Jean Smith’s option grants. The issuing company is in this position:"
    }
  }, {
    "id": "3542524411155305103",
    "list": {
      "isOrdered": true,
      "item": [{
        "text": "Any future ISO option grants issued to Jean will not be automatically bifurcated into an ISO/NSO split by Carta. The underlying shares of any ISO option grants issued to Jean will be all-ISO until a legal administrator in the company reviews and edits the grant via the grant editor.",
        "originalText": "Any future ISO option grants issued to Jean will not be automatically bifurcated into an ISO/NSO split by Carta. The underlying shares of any ISO option grants issued to Jean will be all-ISO until a legal administrator in the company reviews and edits the grant via the grant editor."
      }, {
        "text": "Modifying the vesting schedule of Jean’s ISO option grants in a way that changes tranche-level quantities (e.g. increase quantity via vesting acceleration or decrease quantity via partial cancellation) will reset all tranches of the modified grant to be all-ISO. If tranche-level quantities are changed, it’s impossible for Carta to accurately guess which shares should be ISO versus NSO. A legal administrator will need to review and re-edit the affected grant after the vesting schedule modification.",
        "originalText": "Modifying the vesting schedule of Jean’s ISO option grants in a way that changes tranche-level quantities (e.g. increase quantity via vesting acceleration or decrease quantity via partial cancellation) will reset all tranches of the modified grant to be all-ISO. If tranche-level quantities are changed, it’s impossible for Carta to accurately guess which shares should be ISO versus NSO. A legal administrator will need to review and re-edit the affected grant after the vesting schedule modification."
      }, {
        "text": "Updating the FMV for your company in Carta will not reset any grants to be all-ISO, but the underlying value of the tranches in Jean’s ISO option grant have changed and will likely require review and re-editing via the grant editor.",
        "originalText": "Updating the FMV for your company in Carta will not reset any grants to be all-ISO, but the underlying value of the tranches in Jean’s ISO option grant have changed and will likely require review and re-editing via the grant editor."
      }, {
        "text": "Canceling one or more of Jean’s ISO option grants will not reset any grants to be all-ISO. Instead, Carta will automatically zero-out the quantities in all tranches that become exercisable after the year in which the cancellation took place, per the IRS rule around the treatment of option grant cancellation.",
        "originalText": "Canceling one or more of Jean’s ISO option grants will not reset any grants to be all-ISO. Instead, Carta will automatically zero-out the quantities in all tranches that become exercisable after the year in which the cancellation took place, per the IRS rule around the treatment of option grant cancellation."
      }]
    }
  }]
}

{
