{
  "id": "-829634279659699148",
  "subject": {
    "id": "-829634279659699148",
    "text": {
      "text": "Generating the Forfeiture Rate Report"
    }
  },
  "linked": [{
    "id": "-1815421262884390338",
    "text": {
      "text": "When a company issues equity awards to their employees, ASC 718 requires that the company apply a reasonable forfeiture rate to properly accrue stock-based compensation expenses. Experts established various ways to determine forfeiture rates. Some forfeiture rates are applied annually, semi-annually, and some are applied quarterly. Regardless of the application, developing a reliable forfeiture rate requires professional judgment based on historical data and what the company expects to see in the future.  To comply with the guidance, Carta’s SBC expense reports utilize a forfeiture rate to account for the percentage of shares the company expects will never vest and, therefore, will not record expenses [1].  This means that entities must come up with a way to predict or estimate future forfeitures. Carta helps companies solve this problem by providing a forfeiture rate report which collects historical information regarding awards issued, terminated, and forfeited.",
      "originalText": "When a company issues equity awards to their employees, ASC 718 requires that the company apply a reasonable forfeiture rate to properly accrue stock-based compensation expenses. Experts established various ways to determine forfeiture rates. Some forfeiture rates are applied annually, semi-annually, and some are applied quarterly. Regardless of the application, developing a reliable forfeiture rate requires professional judgment based on historical data and what the company expects to see in the future.<br><br>To comply with the guidance, Carta’s SBC expense reports utilize a forfeiture rate to account for the percentage of shares the company expects will never vest and, therefore, will not record expenses <a href=\"https://support.carta.com/s/article/generate-forfeiture#note\">[1]</a>.<br><br>This means that entities must come up with a way to predict or estimate future forfeitures. Carta helps companies solve this problem by providing a forfeiture rate report which collects historical information regarding awards issued, terminated, and forfeited."
    }
  }, {
    "id": "-3018708412110705891",
    "list": {
      "isOrdered": true,
      "item": [{
        "text": "Navigate to Capitalization > Reporting (for private companies),  carta/public/11/images/8629344872101364868_xn_EwKFvIMdwjMRpjEYxjeoBW79KefKUg8ZZwK66ul0JOjQG22h1YRoXVVcgYWzbACD9ns4PII1OKaFaSXEB5ce4L-cycUIzUH8Fyj9CbDO6ierR3eKnL8BmISeWeROGr0lkz7ck    Or Reports(for public companies).  carta/public/11/images/6954015402971817136_VNyLjREIL4Msf98WmRu45B_CKbc-gRdlaHR7xoNgmTTJ_i-MZuWAE0YeMWeZ3EB2PdUd4G_0zNTNvWhdw57kt1os1IU3llxqXXfagek-mf-58NUNIv_2B7U9TO3k6-hLoIJohlDL",
        "originalText": "Navigate to Capitalization &gt; Reporting (for private companies),<br> <img height=\"142\" src=\"carta/public/11/images/8629344872101364868_xn_EwKFvIMdwjMRpjEYxjeoBW79KefKUg8ZZwK66ul0JOjQG22h1YRoXVVcgYWzbACD9ns4PII1OKaFaSXEB5ce4L-cycUIzUH8Fyj9CbDO6ierR3eKnL8BmISeWeROGr0lkz7ck\" width=\"528\"><br> <br> Or Reports (for public companies).<br> <img height=\"75\" src=\"carta/public/11/images/6954015402971817136_VNyLjREIL4Msf98WmRu45B_CKbc-gRdlaHR7xoNgmTTJ_i-MZuWAE0YeMWeZ3EB2PdUd4G_0zNTNvWhdw57kt1os1IU3llxqXXfagek-mf-58NUNIv_2B7U9TO3k6-hLoIJohlDL\" width=\"528\"><br> &nbsp;",
        "associatedImage": {
          "url": "carta/public/11/images/6954015402971817136_VNyLjREIL4Msf98WmRu45B_CKbc-gRdlaHR7xoNgmTTJ_i-MZuWAE0YeMWeZ3EB2PdUd4G_0zNTNvWhdw57kt1os1IU3llxqXXfagek-mf-58NUNIv_2B7U9TO3k6-hLoIJohlDL"
        }
      }, {
        "text": "In the Terminations folder, click Forfeiture report.  carta/public/11/images/8264652922427977336_9MERnjp2KKx1OUke5VuFY7838W6CRmnY5CeC5tkzTvPc02wo1Y4hGgg2o9EoK_wc0qVqr7lB6fqMjtArQNRSI-mQVbAad15Hsf7tg4kKOl7JhXZ52IvhU6kNzT3wsMtb_yCZyJ3X",
        "originalText": "In the Terminations folder, click Forfeiture report.<br> <img height=\"239\" src=\"carta/public/11/images/8264652922427977336_9MERnjp2KKx1OUke5VuFY7838W6CRmnY5CeC5tkzTvPc02wo1Y4hGgg2o9EoK_wc0qVqr7lB6fqMjtArQNRSI-mQVbAad15Hsf7tg4kKOl7JhXZ52IvhU6kNzT3wsMtb_yCZyJ3X\" width=\"526\"><br> &nbsp;",
        "associatedImage": {
          "url": "carta/public/11/images/8264652922427977336_9MERnjp2KKx1OUke5VuFY7838W6CRmnY5CeC5tkzTvPc02wo1Y4hGgg2o9EoK_wc0qVqr7lB6fqMjtArQNRSI-mQVbAad15Hsf7tg4kKOl7JhXZ52IvhU6kNzT3wsMtb_yCZyJ3X"
        }
      }, {
        "text": "Enter the As of date to pull the data. If the defaulted date, As of today, is selected, then Carta will export the data for all awards issued and updated as of today's date. The excel export will allow you to enter in start and end dates later.  carta/public/11/images/637212700578849723_-EmB1gG56V0oMm5uW3FYYB_pf2hF9A3Dx2J2XbZUxHjm1UndtZAP2XBIdZ19i0MVML74b7lCXB5zWqN4p98JIj8wuHIJSVcr6UP06GuyD667LpeMFDj-WO6quVwoQ1YhR0Uy5agx",
        "originalText": "Enter the As of date to pull the data. If the defaulted date, As of today, is selected, then Carta will export the data for all awards issued and updated as of today's date. The excel export will allow you to enter in start and end dates later.<br> <img height=\"266\" src=\"carta/public/11/images/637212700578849723_-EmB1gG56V0oMm5uW3FYYB_pf2hF9A3Dx2J2XbZUxHjm1UndtZAP2XBIdZ19i0MVML74b7lCXB5zWqN4p98JIj8wuHIJSVcr6UP06GuyD667LpeMFDj-WO6quVwoQ1YhR0Uy5agx\" width=\"433\"><br> &nbsp;",
        "associatedImage": {
          "url": "carta/public/11/images/637212700578849723_-EmB1gG56V0oMm5uW3FYYB_pf2hF9A3Dx2J2XbZUxHjm1UndtZAP2XBIdZ19i0MVML74b7lCXB5zWqN4p98JIj8wuHIJSVcr6UP06GuyD667LpeMFDj-WO6quVwoQ1YhR0Uy5agx"
        }
      }, {
        "text": "Click Export to Excel. When the report is finished generating, it will appear in the Downloads folder and a green notification will appear in the top right hand corner of the page prompting the download.  carta/public/11/images/5728548511983059594_B4dRlLk4qiVSu91CG8mSwVjJnIrGbCin4GeZya-PPS28TVnnr4iZvJaCb6lwCkAWKKNUJe5T09DAeT7XVAh3No4Q0x0EMfg2VNPgJHVtTYhm1jhVv-EHR3hUY14v9mWdw4wfgzOO",
        "originalText": "Click Export to Excel. When the report is finished generating, it will appear in the Downloads folder and a green notification will appear in the top right hand corner of the page prompting the download.<br> <img height=\"188\" src=\"carta/public/11/images/5728548511983059594_B4dRlLk4qiVSu91CG8mSwVjJnIrGbCin4GeZya-PPS28TVnnr4iZvJaCb6lwCkAWKKNUJe5T09DAeT7XVAh3No4Q0x0EMfg2VNPgJHVtTYhm1jhVv-EHR3hUY14v9mWdw4wfgzOO\" width=\"462\"><br> &nbsp;",
        "associatedImage": {
          "url": "carta/public/11/images/5728548511983059594_B4dRlLk4qiVSu91CG8mSwVjJnIrGbCin4GeZya-PPS28TVnnr4iZvJaCb6lwCkAWKKNUJe5T09DAeT7XVAh3No4Q0x0EMfg2VNPgJHVtTYhm1jhVv-EHR3hUY14v9mWdw4wfgzOO"
        }
      }, {
        "text": "Once downloaded and opened, the three editable dates are highlighted in green.    Both Start Date and End Date should outline the period that may be the most indicative of future forfeitures. Once populated, the data being used in the calculation will only cover grants issued within this period.    As of Date is the date from which the data is to be analyzed. This would generally be today's date but can also be a past date, no earlier than the End Date. If you are looking to be able to use awards granted and/or forfeited up until today's date, it is recommended using today's date as the As of Date.  carta/public/11/images/4000998450607052298_Sg4jW6ABl51G3Tncl4E-IazQ-nCj1KQU2AsQecLkEymrEagFB-acyBD-CwmEdxWqXT5JV_jE0IHVgDr63xsyiY5HvJQJFaALf_fzm3COW1rv8bEf0NXAdm-ZdDJL3E_alKytXCom",
        "originalText": "Once downloaded and opened, the three editable dates are highlighted in green.<br> <br> Both Start Date and End Date should outline the period that may be the most indicative of future forfeitures. Once populated, the data being used in the calculation will only cover grants issued within this period.<br> <br> As of Date is the date from which the data is to be analyzed. This would generally be today's date but can also be a past date, no earlier than the End Date. If you are looking to be able to use awards granted and/or forfeited up until today's date, it is recommended using today's date as the As of Date.<br> <img height=\"376\" src=\"carta/public/11/images/4000998450607052298_Sg4jW6ABl51G3Tncl4E-IazQ-nCj1KQU2AsQecLkEymrEagFB-acyBD-CwmEdxWqXT5JV_jE0IHVgDr63xsyiY5HvJQJFaALf_fzm3COW1rv8bEf0NXAdm-ZdDJL3E_alKytXCom\" width=\"524\"><br> &nbsp;",
        "associatedImage": {
          "url": "carta/public/11/images/4000998450607052298_Sg4jW6ABl51G3Tncl4E-IazQ-nCj1KQU2AsQecLkEymrEagFB-acyBD-CwmEdxWqXT5JV_jE0IHVgDr63xsyiY5HvJQJFaALf_fzm3COW1rv8bEf0NXAdm-ZdDJL3E_alKytXCom"
        }
      }, {
        "text": "Once all dates are populated, a recommended forfeiture rate will populate in the red row under the column labeled Annualized Forfeiture Rate. This can be inserted into the applicable years within the Create a new report modal, then click Generate Reports.    The forfeiture rate is a forward-looking projection and company historical data may not always be indicative of future forfeitures. The best practice is to supplement the calculated forfeiture rate with known future business events and professional judgment and adjust the forfeiture rate accordingly.",
        "originalText": "Once all dates are populated, a recommended forfeiture rate will populate in the red row under the column labeled Annualized Forfeiture Rate. This can be inserted into the applicable years within the <a href=\"https://support.carta.com/s/article/create-asc718-report\" style=\"text-decoration: none;\" target=\"_blank\">Create a new report modal</a>, then click Generate Reports.<br> <br> The forfeiture rate is a forward-looking projection and company historical data may not always be indicative of future forfeitures. The best practice is to supplement the calculated forfeiture rate with known future business events and professional judgment and adjust the forfeiture rate accordingly."
      }]
    }
  }, {
    "id": "-4530081245180215934",
    "text": {
      "text": "NOTE: Carta recommends that allForfeiture Rate spreadsheets are saved after you are finished using them to provide audit support and justification for your use of that specified value/rate. These values can be changed if you add, modify, or terminate a historical grant so it is important to keep a copy of the specific report used to estimate the forfeiture rate.   Recall that ASC 718-10-55-30 states the following: carta/public/11/images/2388806751990453446_ANk6YyaA4r8KvhvjUhMAkndI0kl6gRX8szdErm8NqQBcluODtBe3S4SvpRlgyzrprWDiCFTz08-cMZ4Tf-HE5o55da4ZD_o8prHAybzI9IEW1wwCiaaqI4QujhByNMVeg33DPjLu  Thus, compensation cost is recorded alongside when shares vest. For option grants that terminate prior to vesting, no compensation cost will be recorded and any historically recognized compensation cost associated with that award will be reversed in the period during which the grant was terminated unvested.",
