  "linked": [{
    "id": "3074792448258307500",
    "text": {
      "text": "In Carta, we define a Rule 701 share as any security that was issued withRule 701 selected as theFederal Exemption. More information on issuing securities.  Our worksheet contains separate tabs for each security type, listing the included securities for reference. carta/public/11/images/3619518301058268650_rtaImage",
      "originalText": "In Carta, we define a Rule 701 share as any security that was issued with Rule 701&nbsp;selected as the&nbsp;Federal Exemption. <a href=\"https://support.carta.com/s/article/workflow-securities\" target=\"_blank\"><u>More information on issuing securities</u></a>.&nbsp;<br><br>Our worksheet contains separate tabs for each security type, listing the included securities for reference.<br><img alt=\"\" src=\"carta/public/11/images/3619518301058268650_rtaImage\" style=\"width: 456px;height: 36px;\"><br>&nbsp;",
      "associatedImage": {
        "url": "carta/public/11/images/3619518301058268650_rtaImage"
      }
    }
  }, {
    "id": "6155722462224006830",
    "list": {
      "item": [{
        "text": "Canceled or expired securities are not included in the Rule 701 check.Only the stock that was originally issued under Rule 701 is included. Transferred and balance stock certificates are excluded.Common certificates resulting from the exercise or settlement of Rule 701 equity awards are included. The exercised portion of the equity award is reported underCommon shares issuable upon exercise of Rule 701 option grants/RSUs to avoid double counting.Preferred shares and warrants that exercised into preferred are grouped together underPreferred shares issued or issuable upon exercise of Rule 701 warrants.",
        "originalText": "Canceled or expired securities are not included in the Rule 701 check.  Only the stock that was originally issued under Rule 701 is included. Transferred and balance stock certificates are excluded. Common certificates resulting from the exercise or settlement of Rule 701 equity awards are included. The exercised portion of the equity award is reported under Common shares issuable upon exercise of Rule 701 option grants/RSUs to avoid double counting. Preferred shares and warrants that exercised into preferred are grouped together under Preferred shares issued or issuable upon exercise of Rule 701 warrants.  "
      }, {
        "text": "In Carta, outstanding shares are defined as securities that were not issued under Rule 701.",
        "originalText": "In Carta, outstanding shares are defined as securities that were not issued under Rule 701."
      }]
    }
  }]
}

