  }, {
    "id": "-5273688973524544551",
    "list": {
      "item": [{
        "text": "Row 10 - 17 represents the securities issued in Carta as of the report end date, meeting all of the following criteria:(1) Original issue date is within the report period,(2) Federal exemption is Rule 701,(3) remain outstanding as of the report period end date.We have included separate tabs for each security type, listing the securities included in the report for reference.",
        "originalText": "Row 10 - 17 represents the securities issued in Carta as of the report end date, meeting all of the following criteria:  (1) Original issue date is within the report period, (2) Federal exemption is Rule 701, (3) remain outstanding as of the report period end date. &nbsp; We have included separate tabs for each security type, listing the securities included in the report for reference.  <br> &nbsp;"
      }, {
        "text": "Row 11 (Common shares issuable upon exercise of Rule 701 option grants/RSUs): Includes option grants and RSUs that were both (1) issued during the report period and (2) remain outstanding as of the report end date. If an award has been both (a) issued and (b) partially exercised or settled within the report period, the remaining, outstanding portion of the option grant or RSU is reported in Row 11.    Shares of common stock that were both (a) granted and (b) exercised or settled within the 12 month period are reported in Row 13 below, to prevent double counting. This method allows Carta to make the issued and outstanding awards whole for purposes of Test 1 (Aggregate dollar value of Rule 701 shares < $1M), while automatically excluding any underlying shares that were canceled, terminated or expired during the report period.",
        "originalText": "Row 11 (Common shares issuable upon exercise of Rule 701 option grants/RSUs): Includes option grants and RSUs that were both (1) issued during the report period and (2) remain outstanding as of the report end date. &nbsp;If an award has been both (a) issued and (b) partially exercised or settled within the report period, the remaining, outstanding portion of the option grant or RSU is reported in Row 11.<br> <br> Shares of common stock that were both (a) granted and (b) exercised or settled within the 12 month period are reported in Row 13 below, to prevent double counting. &nbsp;This method allows Carta to make the issued and outstanding awards whole for purposes of Test 1 (Aggregate dollar value of Rule 701 shares &lt; $1M), while automatically excluding any underlying shares that were canceled, terminated or expired during the report period.<br> &nbsp;"
      }, {
        "text": "Row 12 (Common shares issuable under Rule 701 warrants): Warrants should be treated similarly to options (they also have to be exercised/purchased). Rule 701 only applies to natural persons, thus awards issued to entities (i.e., a consulting firm providing services) should not be included here.",
        "originalText": "Row 12 (Common shares issuable under Rule 701 warrants): Warrants should be treated similarly to options (they also have to be exercised/purchased). Rule 701 only applies to natural persons, thus awards issued to entities (i.e., a consulting firm providing services) should not be included here.<br> &nbsp;"
