    "text": {
      "text": "Enabling Online Transactions (Non-US Companies)"
    }
  },
  "linked": [{
    "id": "-6843668441165036174",
    "text": {
      "text": "Private companies incorporated inBermuda,Canada, Cayman Island,or Singapore can enable Option Exercises to allow optionholders to initiate exercise requests from Carta. After exercises are approved, optionholders will receive wire instructions as provided by the company. Non-US optionholders cannot process exercise transactions via ACH due to regulatory restrictions.  NOTE: Certificate issue dates correspond with the date company admins mark the exercises as paid.",
      "originalText": "Private companies incorporated in Bermuda,&nbsp;Canada, Cayman Island, or Singapore can enable Option Exercises to allow optionholders to initiate exercise requests from Carta. After exercises are approved, optionholders will receive wire instructions as provided by the company. Non-US optionholders cannot process exercise transactions via ACH due to regulatory restrictions.<br><br>NOTE: Certificate issue dates correspond with the date company admins mark the exercises as paid."
    }
