{
  "id": "-3809992806562483349",
  "subject": {
    "id": "-3809992806562483349",
    "text": {
      "text": "Tax mobility"
    },
    "signals": [{
      "valueL": "3"
    }]
  },
  "linked": [{
    "id": "4371320008418594117",
    "text": {
      "text": "In theStakeholder ledger, company administrators can create a history or timeline of addresses for each stakeholder. Each stakeholder address in this history will be tied to an effective date, which represents the date on which the stakeholder moved to the address. If tax mobility is enabled, Carta’s tax system will use these effectively dated addresses to estimate option exercise withholding amounts by comparing the vesting period of the to-be-exercised option grant to the effectively dated addresses for the stakeholder.",
      "originalText": "In the Stakeholder ledger, company administrators can create a <a href=\"https://support.carta.com/s/article/managing-stakeholder-addresses\" target=\"_blank\"><u>history or timeline of addresses for each stakeholder</u></a>. Each stakeholder address in this history will be tied to an effective date, which represents the date on which the stakeholder moved to the address. If tax mobility is enabled, Carta’s tax system will use these effectively dated addresses to estimate option exercise withholding amounts by comparing the vesting period of the to-be-exercised option grant to the effectively dated addresses for the stakeholder."
    }
  }, {
    "id": "-6301938016139261075",
    "text": {
      "text": "To turn tax mobility on for your company, navigate toCompliance > Tax rulesand toggle the feature on the upper right corner.\n",
      "originalText": "<br>To turn tax mobility on for your company, navigate to Compliance &gt; Tax rules&nbsp;and toggle the feature on the upper right corner.<br>"
    }
  }, {
    "id": "5172326372923350169",
    "text": {
      "text": "carta/public/11/images/5804996762652505349_q-fI15wqiyPfsi0H98oJL5zs0AhDPOiOwB9HriqoEEOQ4izoxBzrZEuQT-48XJjLsezkOJQ-zNsocxAz2YpN5XLluqiy1R3UqlfRmJ_gijZyMPOWEnK6o2ETN9VLXJKmuw-4VHSw",
      "originalText": "<img height=\"256\" src=\"carta/public/11/images/5804996762652505349_q-fI15wqiyPfsi0H98oJL5zs0AhDPOiOwB9HriqoEEOQ4izoxBzrZEuQT-48XJjLsezkOJQ-zNsocxAz2YpN5XLluqiy1R3UqlfRmJ_gijZyMPOWEnK6o2ETN9VLXJKmuw-4VHSw\" width=\"478.35600998015633\">",
      "associatedImage": {
        "url": "carta/public/11/images/5804996762652505349_q-fI15wqiyPfsi0H98oJL5zs0AhDPOiOwB9HriqoEEOQ4izoxBzrZEuQT-48XJjLsezkOJQ-zNsocxAz2YpN5XLluqiy1R3UqlfRmJ_gijZyMPOWEnK6o2ETN9VLXJKmuw-4VHSw"
      }
    },
    "signals": [{
      "key": "FontBolded",
      "valueB": true
    }]
  }, {
    "id": "5792384862980532583",
    "text": {
      "text": "You can disable tax mobility if your company chooses not to use the feature. When tax mobility is disabled, Carta’s tax system will use the most recent address in a stakeholder’s address history as the applicable tax jurisdiction when estimating taxes.",
      "originalText": "You can disable tax mobility if your company chooses not to use the feature. When tax mobility is disabled, Carta’s tax system will use the most recent address in a stakeholder’s address history as the applicable tax jurisdiction when estimating taxes."
    }
  }, {
    "id": "-2539718391324356021",
    "text": {
      "text": "If tax mobility is enabled, Carta’s tax system will first look at the vesting period for the to-be-exercised option grant. If the stakeholder has lived in multiple locations during the vesting period based on the effective dates of their addresses, Carta’s tax system will split tax estimates across each jurisdiction depending on whether the stakeholder moved from one US state to another, or from one country to another.  If the stakeholder moved from one US state to another, Carta’s tax system will estimate and split the total tax withholding amount across each jurisdiction based on how long the stakeholder lived in each jurisdiction. The longer a stakeholder lived in a location during the vesting period, the more tax will be apportioned to that jurisdiction at time of exercise.  If the stakeholder moved from one country to another, Carta’s tax system will estimate the total tax owed to each jurisdiction and disregard country-specific treaty rules, as international tax treaties are currently unsupported by Carta’s tax system.",
      "originalText": "If tax mobility is enabled, Carta’s tax system will first look at the vesting period for the to-be-exercised option grant. If the stakeholder has lived in multiple locations during the vesting period based on the effective dates of their addresses, Carta’s tax system will split tax estimates across each jurisdiction depending on whether the stakeholder moved from one US state to another, or from one country to another.<br><br>If the stakeholder moved from one US state to another, Carta’s tax system will estimate and split the total tax withholding amount across each jurisdiction based on how long the stakeholder lived in each jurisdiction. The longer a stakeholder lived in a location during the vesting period, the more tax will be apportioned to that jurisdiction at time of exercise.<br><br>If the stakeholder moved from one country to another, Carta’s tax system will estimate the total tax owed to each jurisdiction and disregard country-specific treaty rules, as international tax treaties are currently unsupported by Carta’s tax system."
    }
  }, {
    "id": "2760904580752775001",
    "text": {
      "text": "NOTE: While these methods will not produce perfectly accurate tax estimates due to special tax rules like treaties and reciprocity, it will likely ensure that all relevant tax jurisdictions are added as part of the exercise request. In all cases, company admins will have the ability to adjust the specific tax amounts per jurisdiction during the exercise approval step.  Speak with a tax professional to get more information on whether or not your company should be using the tax mobility feature.",
      "originalText": "NOTE: While these methods will not produce perfectly accurate tax estimates due to special tax rules like treaties and reciprocity, it will likely ensure that all relevant tax jurisdictions are added as part of the exercise request. In all cases, company admins will have the ability to <a href=\"https://support.carta.com/s/article/manage-tax-withholding#override-carta-est-tax-withholdings\"><u>adjust the specific tax amounts per jurisdiction during the exercise approval step.</u></a><br><br>Speak with a tax professional to get more information on whether or not your company should be using the tax mobility feature."
    }
  }]
}

{
  "id": "4075327628474497072",
  "subject": {
    "id": "4075327628474497072",
    "text": {
      "text": "Exercise approval banner"
    },
    "signals": [{
      "valueL": "3"
    }]
  },
  "linked": [{
    "id": "675293389283191428",
    "text": {
      "text": "Administrators for companies issuing NSOs, RSUs, or other securities with tax withholding implications may notice the following orange banner when approving an option exercise submitted by a stakeholder. The banner will appear if the company-managed stakeholder address stored in the Stakeholder ledger is missing or invalid.  The purpose of this banner is to remind the administrator thataccurately withholding tax is the legal responsibility of the issuing company. If the address for the stakeholder is incomplete or needs to be updated in the company’s records, the issuing company is not fulfilling this responsibility. carta/public/11/images/8097449483142733932_TnEmss8OCAwH_lR2uKXJV1Tc1P-ywKCoBcrxQa6ui7r7yHe1_xQe6xKiQkqFT1xT5f0WFbZZntTxzz0hDJMphyzlbQ4NqzRLlgaTUiHY4z5X7D8JJ0y9jFanv24ObHHYmppSqcs_",
      "originalText": "Administrators for companies issuing NSOs, RSUs, or other securities with tax withholding implications may notice the following orange banner when approving an option exercise submitted by a stakeholder. The banner will appear if the company-managed stakeholder address stored in the Stakeholder ledger is missing or invalid.<br><br>The purpose of this banner is to remind the administrator that accurately withholding tax is the legal responsibility of the issuing company. If the address for the stakeholder is incomplete or needs to be updated in the company’s records, the issuing company is not fulfilling this responsibility.<br><img height=\"171\" src=\"carta/public/11/images/8097449483142733932_TnEmss8OCAwH_lR2uKXJV1Tc1P-ywKCoBcrxQa6ui7r7yHe1_xQe6xKiQkqFT1xT5f0WFbZZntTxzz0hDJMphyzlbQ4NqzRLlgaTUiHY4z5X7D8JJ0y9jFanv24ObHHYmppSqcs_\" width=\"480\">",
      "associatedImage": {
        "url": "carta/public/11/images/8097449483142733932_TnEmss8OCAwH_lR2uKXJV1Tc1P-ywKCoBcrxQa6ui7r7yHe1_xQe6xKiQkqFT1xT5f0WFbZZntTxzz0hDJMphyzlbQ4NqzRLlgaTUiHY4z5X7D8JJ0y9jFanv24ObHHYmppSqcs_"
      }
    }
  }, {
    "id": "5684988543668952464",
    "text": {
      "text": "NOTE: The banner is a reminder rather than a requirement because requiring that a company enter a valid address for a stakeholder before the stakeholder can submit an exercise could punish the stakeholder for something that can only be completed by the company.  The stakeholder’s address is one of the inputs for calculating tax, so administrators should ensure they have complete and accurate stakeholder address records stored in the Stakeholder ledger, ideally before any additional exercise requests are submitted. If the stakeholder’s address is not updated before their next exercise, company administrators will continue to see the orange banner during the approval step.",
      "originalText": "NOTE: The banner is a reminder rather than a requirement because requiring that a company enter a valid address for a stakeholder before the stakeholder can submit an exercise could punish the stakeholder for something that can only be completed by the company.<br><br>The stakeholder’s address is one of the inputs for calculating tax, so administrators should ensure they have complete and accurate stakeholder address records stored in the Stakeholder ledger, ideally before any additional exercise requests are submitted. If the stakeholder’s address is not updated before their next exercise, company administrators will continue to see the orange banner during the approval step."
    }
  }]
}

{
  "id": "6955550147820897015",
  "subject": {
    "id": "6955550147820897015",
    "text": {
      "text": "Overriding Carta-estimated tax amounts"
    },
    "signals": [{
      "valueL": "3"
    }]
  },
  "linked": [{
    "id": "6465737501160110237",
    "text": {
      "text": "Carta will initially estimate exercise-related taxes based on the rates, rules, address information, and year-to-date income information provided by the issuing company. Upon reviewing exercise transactions, administrators can override the amounts that Carta initially calculates.  When reviewing and approving exercises, taxes can be updated in the tax information section of the approval flow. carta/public/11/images/5479261076734956086_Mj1pU28RPU0g42jIGAY2-stKdpH2Ie0vdR8ZcTUBjJCMvMPC1a3bujiTV_LlaSyAQvmqn3ys2XVY3GkZ2bbHC6XV8wZh5mHNE-_8jkVNsFQCJ_cADVLoUqyzfU14W2g8rziilhkM",
      "originalText": "Carta will initially estimate exercise-related taxes based on the rates, rules, address information, and year-to-date income information provided by the issuing company. Upon reviewing exercise transactions, administrators can override the amounts that Carta initially calculates.<br><br>When reviewing and approving exercises, taxes can be updated in the tax information section of the approval flow.<br><img height=\"417\" src=\"carta/public/11/images/5479261076734956086_Mj1pU28RPU0g42jIGAY2-stKdpH2Ie0vdR8ZcTUBjJCMvMPC1a3bujiTV_LlaSyAQvmqn3ys2XVY3GkZ2bbHC6XV8wZh5mHNE-_8jkVNsFQCJ_cADVLoUqyzfU14W2g8rziilhkM\" width=\"346\">",
      "associatedImage": {
        "url": "carta/public/11/images/5479261076734956086_Mj1pU28RPU0g42jIGAY2-stKdpH2Ie0vdR8ZcTUBjJCMvMPC1a3bujiTV_LlaSyAQvmqn3ys2XVY3GkZ2bbHC6XV8wZh5mHNE-_8jkVNsFQCJ_cADVLoUqyzfU14W2g8rziilhkM"
      }
    }
  }, {
    "id": "5424496599647210848",
    "text": {
      "text": "Setting Adjust Manual Exercises toYesallows administrators to overwrite the dollar quantities calculated for each tax category. These values will be used for the ultimate taxes withheld from the stakeholder and the amount that flows to tax reports.  NOTE: Changing the taxes will affect the total funds that the stakeholder will pay for the exercise (including option cost and taxes). While the participant will receive an email notification with the new values, many issuers choose to reach out to the participant directly prior to submitting these changes.",
      "originalText": "Setting Adjust Manual Exercises to Yes allows administrators to overwrite the dollar quantities calculated for each tax category. These values will be used for the ultimate taxes withheld from the stakeholder and the amount that flows to tax reports.<br><br>NOTE: Changing the taxes will affect the total funds that the stakeholder will pay for the exercise (including option cost and taxes). While the participant will receive an email notification with the new values, many issuers choose to reach out to the participant directly prior to submitting these changes."
    }
  }]
}

