{
  "id": "-4289724002539753466",
  "subject": {
    "id": "-4289724002539753466",
    "text": {
      "text": "I've already issued paper certificates. Can I still issue electronic shares?"
    }
  },
  "linked": [{
    "id": "8907368749825269576",
    "text": {
      "text": "For Shareholders:",
      "originalText": " For Shareholders: "
    }
  }, {
    "id": "2773062659381943662",
    "list": {
      "item": [{
        "text": "If your company has previously issued stock certificates in paper form, then electronic issuances issued to you will be marked as issued in paper and will include an affidavit for you to sign indicating that they have either lost or destroyed the paper certificate and are accepting the electronic shares in its place.",
        "originalText": "If your company has previously issued stock certificates in paper form, then electronic issuances issued to you will be marked as issued in paper and&nbsp;will include an affidavit for you to sign indicating that they have either lost or destroyed the paper certificate and are accepting the electronic shares in its place."
      }, {
        "text": "If the electronic certificate has already been accepted, then contact the issuing company who will work with Carta Support to modify the certificate.",
        "originalText": "If the electronic certificate has already been accepted, then <a href=\"https://support.carta.com/s/article/contacting-the-issuer\" target=\"_blank\"><u>contact the issuing company</u></a> who will work with Carta Support&nbsp;to modify the certificate."
      }]
    }
  }, {
    "id": "-5522373473914597748",
    "text": {
      "text": "For Company Admins:",
      "originalText": "For Company Admins:&nbsp; "
    }
  }, {
    "id": "-7319886340482569910",
    "list": {
      "item": [{
        "text": "If the company has previously issued stock certificates in paper form, then let your law firm or onboarding manager know. The issuances will be marked as issued in paper and we will include an affidavit for the shareholders to sign indicating that they have either lost or destroyed the paper certificate and are accepting the electronic shares in its place.",
        "originalText": "If the company has previously issued stock certificates in paper form, then let your law firm or onboarding manager know. The issuances will be marked as issued in paper and we will include an affidavit for the shareholders to sign indicating that they have either lost or destroyed the paper certificate and are accepting the electronic shares in its place."
      }, {
        "text": "If you have already imported the company and would still like them to be marked as paper, contact your onboarding manager.",
        "originalText": "If you have already imported the company and would still like them to be marked as paper,&nbsp;contact your onboarding manager."
      }, {
        "text": "Transactions such as repurchases and transfers cannot be reflected on the cap table if the security has been flagged as issued as paper.",
