{
  "id": "-1778291548455060115",
  "subject": {
    "id": "-1778291548455060115",
    "text": {
      "text": "Reverse cancellations and repurchases"
    }
  },
  "linked": [{
    "id": "3115333754697174597",
    "list": {
      "isOrdered": true,
      "item": [{
        "text": "To reverse a certificate cancellation, navigate to Securities > Shares page.",
        "originalText": "To reverse a certificate&nbsp;cancellation, navigate to Securities &gt; Shares page."
      }, {
        "text": "Search for desired canceled/repurchased certificate, click on the V button on the right side of its row, and select Reverse cancellation.  carta/public/11/images/7778628650694683762_rtaImage",
        "originalText": "Search for desired canceled/repurchased certificate, click on the V button on the right side of its row, and select Reverse cancellation.<br> <img alt=\"\" src=\"carta/public/11/images/7778628650694683762_rtaImage\">",
        "associatedImage": {
          "url": "carta/public/11/images/7778628650694683762_rtaImage"
        }
      }, {
        "text": "In the modal, you will select a reason for reversal, from a dropdown, and confirm the information. If Other is selected, you will need to write in the reason, which will be saved on the security once the cancellation is reversed. If you are reversing a certificate with certificate resulting from a partial repurchase, the resulting certificate will be deleted. Click Reverse cancellation to complete the transaction reversal.    NOTE: Only unaccepted certificates can be deleted. If a resulting certificate is accepted, submit a case via Carta's Help Center. Once the holder confirms, the support team will be able to retract the certificate and complete the repurchase reversal. Learn more about Carta's Help Center.  carta/public/11/images/8265107915548217682_rtaImage",
        "originalText": "In the modal, you will select a reason for reversal, from a dropdown, and confirm the information. If Other is selected, you will need to write in the reason, which will be saved on the security once the cancellation is reversed. If you are reversing a certificate with certificate resulting from a partial repurchase, the resulting certificate will be deleted. Click Reverse cancellation&nbsp;to complete the transaction reversal.<br> <br> NOTE: Only unaccepted certificates can be deleted. If a resulting certificate is accepted, submit a case via <a href=\"https://app.carta.com/profiles/update?help=true\" target=\"_blank\"><u>Carta's Help Center</u></a>. Once the holder confirms, the support team will be able to retract the certificate and complete the repurchase reversal.&nbsp;<a href=\"https://support.carta.com/s/article/carta-help-center\" target=\"_blank\"><u>Learn more about Carta's Help Center</u></a>.<br> <img alt=\"\" src=\"carta/public/11/images/8265107915548217682_rtaImage\">",
        "associatedImage": {
          "url": "carta/public/11/images/8265107915548217682_rtaImage"
        }
      }, {
        "text": "Once reversed, the original security will show as outstanding in the ledger and a note will be added to the security under the Documents and notes section. No notifications are sent out when reversing cancellations or repurchases.  carta/public/11/images/3715026406039031900_rtaImage",
        "originalText": "Once reversed, the original security will show as outstanding in the ledger and a note will be added to the security under the Documents and notes section. No notifications are sent out when reversing cancellations or repurchases.<br> <img alt=\"\" src=\"carta/public/11/images/3715026406039031900_rtaImage\">",
        "associatedImage": {
          "url": "carta/public/11/images/3715026406039031900_rtaImage"
        }
      }]
    }
  }, {
    "id": "6651385985152860947",
    "text": {
      "text": "NOTE: This feature doesnot include reversing transfers, exercises or conversions at this time.",
      "originalText": "NOTE: This feature does not include reversing transfers, exercises or conversions at this time."
    }
  }]
}

{
  "id": "-4807325442506102558",
  "subject": {
    "id": "-4807325442506102558",
    "text": {
      "text": "Fair Market Value (FMV) Table"
    }
  },
  "linked": [{
    "id": "8976504431180632753",
    "text": {
      "text": "In order to generate the expense reports, an accurate record of the historical 409a fair market value (FMV) must be saved on the Carta platform. The FMV is used as an input into the valuation models used to value the option grants and restricted stock. As such, this information is crucial to record the accurate expense amounts. The Carta Expensing Tool uses the FMV information that is stored on theCompliance > 409A page. You can add non-Carta board approved fair market values to the 409a page by following the directions here. carta/public/11/images/6131240937660765218_rtaImage",
      "originalText": "In order to generate the expense reports, an accurate record of the historical 409a fair market value (FMV) must be saved on the Carta platform. The FMV is used as an input into the valuation models used to value the option grants and restricted stock. As such, this information is crucial to record the accurate expense amounts. The Carta Expensing Tool uses the FMV information that is stored on the&nbsp;Compliance &gt; 409A&nbsp;page.&nbsp;You can add non-Carta board approved fair market values to the 409a page by following the directions <a href=\"https://support.carta.com/s/article/add-a-fair-market-value\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>.<br><img alt=\"\" src=\"carta/public/11/images/6131240937660765218_rtaImage\">",
      "associatedImage": {
        "url": "carta/public/11/images/6131240937660765218_rtaImage"
      }
    }
  }, {
    "id": "3403569801200655326",
    "list": {
      "isOrdered": true,
      "item": [{
        "text": "You can edit, delete, or add FMVs specific to expense reporting purposes on the FMV Table during the expense generation process when you Create a new report. To locate this page, navigate to Compliance > Expense accounting and click  Create a new report process.  carta/public/11/images/7774551106916732196_rtaImage",
        "originalText": "You can edit, delete, or add FMVs specific to expense reporting purposes on the FMV Table during the expense generation process when you Create a new report. To locate this page, navigate to Compliance &gt; Expense accounting and click  Create a new report process.<br> <img alt=\"\" src=\"carta/public/11/images/7774551106916732196_rtaImage\">",
        "associatedImage": {
          "url": "carta/public/11/images/7774551106916732196_rtaImage"
        }
      }, {
        "text": "In the popup, you will see that Fair Market Value is a necessary step in creating a new report.  carta/public/11/images/2353511783579476520_rtaImage",
        "originalText": "In the popup, you will see that Fair Market Value is a necessary step in creating a new report.<br> <img alt=\"\" src=\"carta/public/11/images/2353511783579476520_rtaImage\">",
        "associatedImage": {
          "url": "carta/public/11/images/2353511783579476520_rtaImage"
        }
      }, {
        "text": "After adding and reviewing the public peer companies to be used for the volatility assumption, you will be prompted to review the fair market values.  carta/public/11/images/5244278403388288231_rtaImage",
        "originalText": "After adding and reviewing the public peer companies to be used for the volatility assumption, you will be prompted to review the fair market values.<br> <img alt=\"\" src=\"carta/public/11/images/5244278403388288231_rtaImage\">",
        "associatedImage": {
          "url": "carta/public/11/images/5244278403388288231_rtaImage"
        }
      }, {
        "text": "Note that in order to successfully generate the expense report, you will need to make sure that a FMV is listed on this page that covers the date of the earliest issued award. For companies that did not have a third-party conducted the 409a at this early stage, a board approved FMV is sufficient. You can add additional FMV's for expensing purposes here using the green + option or delete FMVs that do not apply. Be sure to account for any splits that may have occurred by entering all values in post-split format. If you worked with Carta to record the stock split on the platform, the FMVs will already reflect the post-split numbers.    For companies that have multiple share classes of common with equity awards issued out of each share class, our expense reports will allow for an additional layer of visibility on the FMV Table, enabling the expense reports to generate accurate option values based on each grants' underlying share class. When you have multiple underlying share classes, the tool will prompt you to include a value for each common share class as seen below:  carta/public/11/images/4852343355246952458_rtaImage",
        "originalText": "Note that in order to successfully generate the expense report, you will need to make sure that a FMV is listed on this page that covers the date of the earliest issued award. For companies that did not have a third-party conducted the 409a at this early stage, a board approved FMV is sufficient. You can add additional FMV's for expensing purposes here using the green + option or delete FMVs that do not apply. Be sure to account for any splits that may have occurred by&nbsp;entering all values in post-split format. If you worked with Carta to record the stock split on the platform, the FMVs will already reflect the post-split numbers.<br> <br> For companies that have multiple share classes of common with equity awards issued out of each share class, our expense reports will allow for an additional layer of visibility on the FMV Table, enabling the expense reports to generate accurate option values based on each grants' underlying share class. When you have multiple underlying share classes, the tool will prompt you to include a value for each common share class as seen below:<br> <img alt=\"\" src=\"carta/public/11/images/4852343355246952458_rtaImage\">",
        "associatedImage": {
          "url": "carta/public/11/images/4852343355246952458_rtaImage"
        }
      }]
    }
  }]
}

