        "text": "To reverse a certificate cancellation, navigate to Securities > Shares page.",
        "originalText": "To reverse a certificate cancellation, navigate to Securities &gt; Shares page.<br> &nbsp;"
      }, {
        "text": "Search for desired canceled/repurchased certificate, click on the V button on the right side of its row, and select Reverse cancellation.  carta/public/13/images/2075689855246384295_rtaImage",
        "originalText": "Search for desired canceled/repurchased certificate, click on the V button on the right side of its row, and select Reverse cancellation.<br> <img alt=\"\" src=\"carta/public/13/images/2075689855246384295_rtaImage\"><br> &nbsp;",
        "associatedImage": {
          "url": "carta/public/13/images/2075689855246384295_rtaImage"
        }
      }, {
        "text": "In the modal, you will select a reason for reversal, from a dropdown, and confirm the information. If Other is selected, you will need to write in the reason, which will be saved on the security once the cancellation is reversed. If you are reversing a certificate with certificate resulting from a partial repurchase, the resulting certificate will be deleted. Click Reverse cancellation to complete the transaction reversal.    NOTE: Only unaccepted certificates can be deleted. If a resulting certificate is accepted, submit a case via Carta's Help Center. Once the holder confirms, the support team will be able to retract the certificate and complete the repurchase reversal.  carta/public/13/images/8870603366158974518_rtaImage",
        "originalText": "In the modal, you will select a reason for reversal, from a dropdown, and confirm the information. If Other is selected, you will need to write in the reason, which will be saved on the security once the cancellation is reversed. If you are reversing a certificate with certificate resulting from a partial repurchase, the resulting certificate will be deleted. Click Reverse cancellation to complete the transaction reversal.<br> <br> NOTE: Only unaccepted certificates can be deleted. If a resulting certificate is accepted, submit a case via <a href=\"https://app.carta.com/profiles/update?help=true\" target=\"_blank\"><u>Carta's Help Center</u></a>. Once the holder confirms, the support team will be able to retract the certificate and complete the repurchase reversal.<br> <img alt=\"\" src=\"carta/public/13/images/8870603366158974518_rtaImage\"><br> &nbsp;",
        "associatedImage": {
          "url": "carta/public/13/images/8870603366158974518_rtaImage"
        }
      }, {
        "text": "Once reversed, the original security will show as outstanding in the ledger and a note will be added to the security under the Documents and notes section. No notifications are sent out when reversing cancellations or repurchases.  carta/public/13/images/1184897191239589046_rtaImage",
        "originalText": "Once reversed, the original security will show as outstanding in the ledger and a note will be added to the security under the Documents and notes section. No notifications are sent out when reversing cancellations or repurchases.<br> <img alt=\"\" src=\"carta/public/13/images/1184897191239589046_rtaImage\"><br> &nbsp;",
