      "valueL": "4"
    }]
  },
  "linked": [{
    "id": "-6532876629933126680",
    "text": {
      "text": "Named because the percentage ownership of the new investors is fixed/pre-calculated, and all other values are calculated based on that. The result is that the convertibles convert in pre-money (i.e., effectively before the round), resulting in dilution for only the original shareholders. New investors are not diluted by convertibles.  Because the percentage ownership is fixed, the post-money valuation is fixed:",
      "originalText": "Named because the percentage ownership of the new investors is fixed/pre-calculated, and all other values are calculated based on that. The result is that the convertibles convert in pre-money (i.e., effectively before the round), resulting in dilution for only the original shareholders. New investors are not diluted by convertibles.<br><br>Because the percentage ownership is fixed, the post-money valuation is fixed:"
    }
  }, {
    "id": "-7560504191311074238",
    "text": {
      "text": "Post-round valuation = Pre-money valuation + total new investment  Price per share = Pre-money valuation / ( pre-money fully-diluted share count + option pool increase + converted shares )",
      "originalText": "Post-round valuation = Pre-money valuation + total new investment<br><br>Price per share = Pre-money valuation / ( pre-money fully-diluted share count + option pool increase + converted shares )"
    },
    "signals": [{
      "key": "FontBolded",
      "valueB": true
    }]
  }]
}

{
  "id": "-4401555657082746148",
  "subject": {
    "id": "-4401555657082746148",
    "text": {
      "text": "Pre-money (named \"Post-financing dilution\" in round modeling tool)",
      "originalText": "Pre-money&nbsp;(named \"Post-financing dilution\" in round modeling tool)"
    },
    "signals": [{
      "key": "FontBolded",
      "valueB": true
    }, {
      "valueL": "4"
    }]
  },
  "linked": [{
    "id": "1330929926289298628",
    "text": {
      "text": "Named because the effectivePre-money valuation is fixed/pre-calculated, and all other values are calculated based on that. The result is that the convertibles convert in post-money (i.e., effectively after the round), resulting in dilution for both original shareholders and new investors from the convertibles.  Because the pre-money valuation is fixed, the added value from the convertibles gets added to the post-money valuation:",
      "originalText": "Named because the effective Pre-money valuation is fixed/pre-calculated, and all other values are calculated based on that. The result is that the convertibles convert in post-money (i.e., effectively after the round), resulting in dilution for both original shareholders and new investors from the convertibles.<br><br>Because the pre-money valuation is fixed, the added value from the convertibles gets added to the post-money valuation:"
    }
  }, {
    "id": "-8148685518293010252",
    "text": {
      "text": "Post-round valuation = Pre-money valuation + total new investment + converted value  Price per share = Pre-money valuation / ( pre-money fully-diluted share count + option pool increase )",
      "originalText": "Post-round valuation = Pre-money valuation + total new investment + converted value<br><br>Price per share = Pre-money valuation / ( pre-money fully-diluted share count + option pool increase )"
    },
    "signals": [{
      "key": "FontBolded",
      "valueB": true
    }]
  }]
}

