      "text": "Before generating Form 3921 on Carta, you will need to request a TCC from the IRS, which is required to generate Copy A of Form 3921. Here are steps to electronically request a TCC from the IRS.",
      "originalText": "<br>Before generating Form 3921 on Carta, you will need to request a TCC from the IRS, which is required to generate Copy A of Form 3921. <a href=\"https://support.carta.com/s/article/requesting-your-tcc-for-form-3921-3922\" target=\"_blank\"><u>Here are steps to electronically request&nbsp;a TCC from the IRS</u></a>.<br><br>&nbsp;"
    }
  }]
}

{
  "id": "7519482799102638736",
  "subject": {
    "id": "7519482799102638736",
    "text": {
      "text": "FAQs"
    },
    "signals": [{
      "valueL": "2"
    }]
  },
  "linked": [{
    "id": "-4921717493895223185",
    "text": {
      "text": "What do I need to complete Form 3921?",
      "originalText": "What do I need to complete Form 3921?"
    },
    "signals": [{
      "key": "FontBolded",
      "valueB": true
    }]
  }, {
    "id": "8943829422011688338",
    "list": {
      "isOrdered": true,
      "item": [{
        "text": "TCC - this is a Transmitter Control Code the company must request from the IRS to file their electronic Copy A. This number is the same every year, so if the company has previously generated the form they can find this identifier at the top of their previous Copy A.  If the Form 3921 tab is empty then the company has not previously generated the forms on the platform. We do not remove historical data and any previous forms will be listed.",
        "originalText": "TCC&nbsp;- this is a Transmitter Control Code the company must request from the IRS to file their electronic Copy A. This number is the same every year, so if the company has previously generated the form they can find this identifier at the top of their previous Copy A.<br> If the Form 3921 tab is empty then the company has not previously generated the forms on the platform. We do not remove historical data and any previous forms will be listed."
      }, {
        "text": "Stakeholder information - full name, address, social security number, and email. The email is a Carta requirement to distribute 3921s, not an IRS requirement.",
        "originalText": "Stakeholder information - full name, address, social security number, and email. The email is a Carta requirement to distribute 3921s, not an IRS requirement."
      }, {
        "text": "An FMV on file for each of the exercises, as well as the date the form is being generated.  If there is an FMV missing in either of these situations, or they are in the process of obtaining a 409a, the forms will not be generated until this is completed.",
        "originalText": "An FMV on file for each of the exercises, as well as the date the form is being generated.<br> If there is an FMV missing in either of these situations, or they are in the process of obtaining a 409a, the forms will not be generated until this is completed."
      }]
    }
  }, {
    "id": "-7310413753219336081",
    "text": {
      "text": "Is there any information I should update prior to generating Form 3921? It is recommended that you update stakeholder contact information, addresses, and tax information prior to generating your forms. Failure to do so could result in non-delivery of the form to the stakeholder and IRS. Here are instructions for updating stakeholder information.",
      "originalText": "Is there any information I should update prior to generating Form 3921?<br>It is recommended that you update stakeholder contact information, addresses, and tax information prior to generating your forms. Failure to do so could result in non-delivery of the form to the stakeholder and IRS. <a href=\"https://support.carta.com/s/article/bulk-update-stakeholder-details\" target=\"_blank\"><u>Here are instructions for updating stakeholder information</u></a>.<br>&nbsp;"
    },
    "signals": [{
      "key": "FontBolded",
      "valueB": true
    }]
  }, {
    "id": "9077333975429710747",
    "text": {
      "text": "Do we send reminders to the company to generate the forms? Carta does not send reminders.",
      "originalText": "Do we send reminders to the company to generate the forms?<br>Carta does not send reminders.<br>&nbsp;"
    },
    "signals": [{
      "key": "FontBolded",
      "valueB": true
    }]
  }, {
    "id": "-9206856653502857183",
    "text": {
      "text": "There was an error when generating Form 3921s. What could cause this? There are a few common issues that could cause such an error to occur.",
      "originalText": "There was an error when generating Form 3921s. What could cause this?<br>There are a few common issues that could cause such an error to occur."
    },
    "signals": [{
      "key": "FontBolded",
      "valueB": true
    }]
  }, {
    "id": "-8121444619700339037",
    "list": {
      "item": [{
        "text": "If no ISO exercises occurred during the year you are generating the forms for, the reports will fail. Only ISO exercises require a Form 3921 to be filed. If you are aware of ISO exercises that occurred, but are still receiving the error, data could be missing or incorrect for the exercises. Contact Carta Support via Carta's Help Center for additional assistance.",
        "originalText": "If no ISO exercises occurred during the year you are generating the forms for, the reports will fail. Only ISO exercises require a Form 3921 to be filed. If you are aware of ISO exercises that occurred, but are still receiving the error, data could be missing or incorrect for the exercises. Contact Carta Support via Carta's&nbsp;<a href=\"https://support.carta.com/s/article/carta-help-center\" target=\"_blank\">Help Center</a>&nbsp;for additional assistance."
      }, {
        "text": "A current FMV is required to be on record in order to generate Form 3921 forms/reports. Here is more information about having a Carta 409a valuation performed, as well as information pertaining to entering a non-Carta FMV.",
        "originalText": "A current FMV is required to be on record in order to generate Form 3921 forms/reports. <a href=\"https://support.carta.com/s/article/fair-market-value\" target=\"_blank\">Here is more information</a> about having a Carta 409a valuation performed, as well as information pertaining to entering a non-Carta FMV."
      }]
    }
  }, {
    "id": "-5760730786493602084",
    "text": {
      "text": "I regenerated my Form 3921 reports and the information is different from before. What happened? If additional exercise information or stakeholder information was updated on Carta prior to regenerating the forms, the new version of the reports/forms will differ from the previous version based on the updates entered on the platform.",
      "originalText": "<br>I regenerated my Form 3921 reports and the information is different from before. What happened?<br>If additional exercise information or stakeholder information was updated on Carta prior to regenerating the forms, the new version of the reports/forms will differ from the previous version based on the updates entered on the platform.<br>&nbsp;"
    },
    "signals": [{
      "key": "FontBolded",
      "valueB": true
    }]
  }, {
    "id": "-3581713677019915917",
    "text": {
      "text": "I entered manual exercises for ISO grants and they are missing from the Form 3921 reports. Why? The Form 3921 reports need to be regenerated. Follow these steps to regenerate the forms and reports. If you have already filed Copy A with the IRS, a new version will need to be filed for the manual exercises.",
      "originalText": "I entered manual exercises for ISO grants and they are missing from the Form 3921 reports. Why?<br>The Form 3921 reports need to be regenerated. <a href=\"https://support.carta.com/s/article/how-to-regenerate-form-3921\" target=\"_blank\">Follow these steps to regenerate</a> the forms and reports. If you have already filed Copy A with the IRS, a new version will need to be filed for the manual exercises.<br>&nbsp;"
    },
    "signals": [{
      "key": "FontBolded",
      "valueB": true
    }]
  }, {
    "id": "2903820727078326318",
    "text": {
      "text": "Why is this stakeholder showing up on the list of exercises for the year? I don’t see any ISO exercises for them. If they initiated an exercise and the forms were run it is possible the exercise was then either cancelled or the fund transfer failed. In this case, regenerating the report will update the list of stakeholders.  If an exercise was cancelled after the fund transfer was complete then the stakeholder will still show up. If the company’s legal counsel determines this is not necessary then the exercise request type can be changed to NSO to generate the forms and then switched back to ISO.",
      "originalText": "Why is this stakeholder showing up on the list of exercises for the year? I don’t see any ISO exercises for them.<br>If they initiated an exercise and the forms were run it is possible the exercise was then either cancelled or the fund transfer failed. In this case, regenerating the report will update the list of stakeholders.<br><br>If an exercise was cancelled after the fund transfer was complete then the stakeholder will still show up. If the company’s legal counsel determines this is not necessary then the exercise request type can be changed to NSO to generate the forms and then switched back to ISO.<br>&nbsp;"
    },
    "signals": [{
      "key": "FontBolded",
      "valueB": true
    }]
  }, {
    "id": "-8706269331615583468",
    "text": {
      "text": "Why isn’t this stakeholder showing up on the list of exercises for the year? They exercised an ISO option grant. The exercise request is what is used to create the 3921s and there are a few reasons an exercise request may not exist. If this is the case, contact Carta Support.",
      "originalText": "Why isn’t this stakeholder showing up on the list of exercises for the year? They exercised an ISO option grant.<br>The exercise request is what is used to create the 3921s and there are a few reasons an exercise request may not exist. If this is the case, contact Carta Support."
    },
    "signals": [{
      "key": "FontBolded",
      "valueB": true
    }]
  }, {
    "id": "7985313024537873633",
    "list": {
      "item": [{
        "text": "The exercise was input during onboarding - in this case the exercise tool is not used, and if an exercise is not formally processed then an exercise request is not created.",
        "originalText": "The exercise was input during onboarding - in this case the exercise tool is not used, and if an exercise is not formally processed then an exercise request is not created."
      }, {
        "text": "The certificate was retracted to officer signature - the removal of the signature from the company signatory deletes the exercise request.",
        "originalText": "The certificate was retracted to officer signature - the removal of the signature from the company signatory deletes the exercise request."
      }, {
        "text": "The certificate was created manually and linked to the option grant by Carta staff - again, the exercise is not formally processed so no exercise request is created",
        "originalText": "The certificate was created manually and linked to the option grant by Carta staff - again, the exercise is not formally processed so no exercise request is created"
      }]
    }
  }, {
    "id": "-3625894676163261178",
    "text": {
      "text": "The stakeholder exercised an ISO grant, but some or all of the certificate was repurchased. Should they still get a 3921? It's possible that the full quantity of the exercise should in fact be reported on Form 3921, as the surrendered portion would be reported on Form 1099. The best course of action would be to reach out to your tax advisor, and ask them to confirm the best way to complete those forms.",
      "originalText": "The stakeholder exercised an ISO grant, but some or all of the certificate was repurchased. Should they still get a 3921?<br>It's possible that the full quantity of the exercise should in fact be reported on Form 3921, as the surrendered portion would be reported on Form 1099. The best course of action would be to reach out to your tax advisor, and ask them to confirm the best way to complete those forms.<br>&nbsp;"
    },
    "signals": [{
      "key": "FontBolded",
      "valueB": true
    }]
  }, {
    "id": "5785748779832686289",
    "text": {
      "text": "The stakeholder initiated their exercise before the end of the year, but the funds didn’t transfer or exercise approver did not sign off until the next year. Which year should the form be generated? The year the exercise request was initiated. For ACH exercises, Carta recognizes the exercise date as the date the optionee submits the request, therefore the form will be included in the forms for the year the request was initiated. Learn more.",
      "originalText": "The stakeholder initiated their exercise before the end of the year, but the funds didn’t transfer or exercise approver did not sign off until the next year. Which year should the form be generated?<br>The year the exercise request was initiated. For ACH exercises, Carta recognizes the exercise date as the date the optionee submits the request, therefore the form will be included in the forms for the year the request was initiated. <a href=\"https://support.carta.com/s/article/why-this-date-on-ach-exercise\" target=\"_blank\"><u>Learn more</u></a>.<br>&nbsp;"
    },
    "signals": [{
      "key": "FontBolded",
      "valueB": true
    }]
  }, {
    "id": "7116563483933630274",
    "text": {
      "text": "A non-US company issued ISOs to their US based employees, how can they generate 3921s? The company will need to temporarily change their location to the US in order to have the tax ID field listed on their profile, which is required to generate the forms. Exercises from US companies will be listed on the 3921s.",
      "originalText": "A non-US company issued ISOs to their US based employees, how can they generate 3921s?<br>The company will need to temporarily change their location to the US in order to have the tax ID field listed on their profile, which is required to generate the forms. Exercises from US companies will be listed on the 3921s.<br>&nbsp;"
    },
    "signals": [{
      "key": "FontBolded",
      "valueB": true
    }]
  }, {
    "id": "-6028897210058662165",
    "text": {
      "text": "A company issued ISOs to their non-US based employees, how can they generate the forms without SSNs? If the company’s legal counsel has determined that the non-US based employees could receive ISOs the employee will be subject to US taxes. This means they will have a TIN (tax ID number) that can be used to generate the forms.",
      "originalText": "A company issued ISOs to their non-US based employees, how can they generate the forms without SSNs?<br>If the company’s legal counsel has determined that the non-US based employees could receive ISOs the employee will be subject to US taxes. This means they will have a TIN (tax ID number) that can be used to generate the forms.<br>&nbsp;"
    },
    "signals": [{
      "key": "FontBolded",
      "valueB": true
    }]
  }, {
    "id": "7761768569956258733",
    "text": {
      "text": "The forms are generated by exercises or by stakeholder? Exercises. So if a stakeholder has multiple ISO exercises in that calendar year, then a copy will be generated for each exercise.",
      "originalText": "The forms are generated by exercises or by stakeholder?<br>Exercises. So if a stakeholder has multiple ISO exercises in that calendar year, then a copy&nbsp;will be generated for each exercise.<br>&nbsp;"
    },
    "signals": [{
      "key": "FontBolded",
      "valueB": true
    }]
  }, {
    "id": "4105774112906996826",
    "text": {
      "text": "Will forms be generated for pending exercises (still in progress)? No, exercises must be completed prior to generating a Form 3921.",
      "originalText": "Will forms be generated for pending exercises (still in progress)?<br>No, exercises must be completed prior to generating a Form 3921."
    },
    "signals": [{
      "key": "FontBolded",
      "valueB": true
    }]
  }, {
    "id": "8798644548971262000",
    "text": {
      "text": "Form 3921 does not pass the 409A check but the client has a pending Carta 409A. What is it possible to do? Contact with the valuations analyst and check the status of the valuation. The pending valuation can be removed by the analyst and the client can add a board determined FMV to generate the forms.",
      "originalText": "<br>Form&nbsp;3921 does not pass the 409A check but the client has a pending Carta 409A. What is it possible to do?<br>Contact with the valuations analyst and check the status of the valuation. The pending valuation can be removed by the analyst and the client can add a board determined FMV to generate the forms.<br>&nbsp;"
    },
    "signals": [{
      "key": "FontBolded",
      "valueB": true
    }]
  }, {
    "id": "-1598778598447704841",
    "text": {
      "text": "Does Carta file Form 3921 Copy A with the IRS on behalf of the company? No, the IRS prevents Carta from remitting the form on the company’s behalf. Follow the steps outlined in this article to file Copy A electronically with the IRS.",
      "originalText": "Does Carta file Form 3921 Copy A with the IRS on behalf of the company?<br>No, the IRS prevents Carta from remitting the form on the company’s behalf. Follow the steps outlined in <a href=\"https://support.carta.com/s/article/uploading-3921\" target=\"_blank\"><u>this article</u></a> to file Copy A electronically with the IRS.<br>&nbsp;"
    },
    "signals": [{
      "key": "FontBolded",
      "valueB": true
    }]
  }, {
    "id": "-9220744831277597700",
    "text": {
      "text": "I opened a Form 3921 Copy A to review the information and noticed it was a plain text file. Is this normal? Yes, this is the required format to electronically remit the form to the IRS. Carta is unable to generate a paper form submission. To file Copy A via paper to the IRS, the form must be requested from the IRS directly for submission, which is due by February 28.",
      "originalText": "I opened a Form 3921 Copy A to review the information and noticed it was a plain text file. Is this normal?<br>Yes, this is the required format to electronically remit the form to the IRS. Carta is unable to generate a paper form submission. To file Copy A via paper to the IRS, the form must be requested from the<a href=\"https://www.irs.gov/forms-pubs/about-form-3921\" target=\"_blank\"><u> IRS directly</u></a> for submission, which is due by February 28.<br>&nbsp;"
    },
    "signals": [{
      "key": "FontBolded",
      "valueB": true
    }]
  }, {
    "id": "-682252572447127543",
    "text": {
      "text": "Why does Copy B limit to 2 decimal places for exercise price? If you are filing electronically, you probably went through some angst last year relating to rounding shares and/or monetary amounts. Publication 1220 was updated this year to specify that a true round should be used on share amounts. There's still no instruction on how monetary values should be rounded, but it would seem reasonable to do the same thing. Each payment field must contain 12 numeric characters. Each payment amount must contain U.S. dollars and cents. The right-most two positions represent cents in the payment amount fields. Reference page 79: p1220.pdf",
      "originalText": "Why does Copy B limit to 2 decimal places for exercise price?<br>If you are filing electronically, you probably went through some angst last year relating to rounding shares and/or monetary amounts. Publication 1220 was updated this year to specify that a true round should be used on share amounts. There's still no instruction on how monetary values should be rounded, but it would seem reasonable to do the same thing. Each payment field must contain 12 numeric characters. Each payment amount must contain U.S. dollars and cents. The right-most two positions represent cents in the payment amount fields. Reference page 79: <a href=\"https://s3.amazonaws.com/helpscout.net/docs/assets/558b2474e4b01a224b42e68e/attachments/5c50a45d042863543ccc59c7/p1220.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">p1220.pdf</a><br>&nbsp;"
    },
    "signals": [{
      "key": "FontBolded",
      "valueB": true
    }]
  }]
}

{
  "id": "7059888355484221382",
  "subject": {
    "id": "7059888355484221382",
    "text": {
      "text": "Tender Offer FAQ"
    }
  },
  "linked": [{
    "id": "5265588710415925307",
    "text": {
      "text": "Review these frequently asked questions about Tender Offers facilitated on Carta.",
      "originalText": "Review these frequently asked questions about <a href=\"https://carta.com/private-companies/liquidity/\" target=\"_blank\"><u>Tender Offers facilitated on Carta</u></a>."
    }
  }, {
    "id": "-6794407376508745751",
    "text": {
      "text": "What type of transactions can I execute through the Carta tender offer feature? Company Buyback and Secondary.",
      "originalText": "What type of transactions can I execute through the Carta <a href=\"https://blog.carta.com/tender-offer-faq/\" target=\"_blank\">tender offer</a> feature?<br>Company Buyback and Secondary."
    },
    "signals": [{
      "key": "FontBolded",
      "valueB": true
    }]
  }, {
    "id": "-8461084993247891630",
    "text": {
      "text": "How do I set up a tender offer in Carta? Request a demo and pricing with our Relationship Management team. Once a contract is signed, you will be assigned a Project Manager who will work with you to setup and launch the offer.",
      "originalText": "How do I set up a tender offer in Carta?<br>Request a demo and pricing with our Relationship Management team. Once a contract is signed, you will be assigned a Project Manager who will work with you to setup and launch the offer."
    },
    "signals": [{
      "key": "FontBolded",
      "valueB": true
    }]
  }, {
    "id": "-1478176276864176388",
    "text": {
      "text": "How much lead time do we need to set up the tender offer in Carta? Final seller table in Carta required format, offer to purchase, letter of transmittal, and disclosure documents should be provided to Cart at least two weeks prior to the first order date.",
      "originalText": "How much lead time do we need to set up the tender offer in Carta?<br>Final seller table in Carta required format, offer to purchase, letter of transmittal, and disclosure documents should be provided to Cart at least two weeks prior to the first order date."
    },
    "signals": [{
      "key": "FontBolded",
      "valueB": true
    }]
  }, {
    "id": "-1482961060387279168",
    "text": {
      "text": "What does the participant experience look like? Review this article for more information.",
      "originalText": "What does the participant experience look like?<br><a href=\"https://support.carta.com/s/article/participate-tender-offer\" target=\"_blank\"><u>Review this article for more information</u></a>."
    },
    "signals": [{
      "key": "FontBolded",
      "valueB": true
    }]
  }, {
    "id": "3003351421322268560",
    "text": {
      "text": "Can participants execute a cashless exercise? Yes, our tender offer feature is designed for cashless exercise. Once the transaction is settled, we will automatically update the cap table with the exercise and cancellation of the stock certificate.",
      "originalText": "Can participants execute a cashless exercise?<br>Yes, our tender offer feature is designed for cashless exercise. Once the transaction is settled, we will automatically update the cap table with the exercise and cancellation of the stock certificate."
    },
    "signals": [{
      "key": "FontBolded",
      "valueB": true
    }]
  }, {
    "id": "2248155482367626744",
    "text": {
      "text": "How does it work if we don’t allow cashless exercise? Participants will exercise outside of the tender offer via ACH on Carta or manually with company admin. Once the certificate is created, we will add it to the tender offer so the employee can place their order.",
      "originalText": "How does it work if we don’t allow cashless exercise?<br>Participants will exercise outside of the tender offer via ACH on Carta or manually with company admin. Once the certificate is created, we will add it to the tender offer so the employee can place their order."
    },
    "signals": [{
      "key": "FontBolded",
      "valueB": true
    }]
  }, {
    "id": "-6212596879708832416",
    "text": {
      "text": "How many shares are eligible to sell during the Tender Offer? You can find the number of eligible shares to sell in theTransaction overview. Note that this number (see screenshot) in theTransaction Overview page is the total number of shares that you are eligible to sell across all your holdings. carta/public/13/images/5919393131023195261_KX3JTP50nq_xZd2ZamFmu5A8g6vEuI96V4m_-Tpe5KZSi-A1vDlhGNzxxNvujkqr5sbfTjj94tZDHWtg_WvpklWrYHKOQvEbmu5qwMJWS5-XAL5S7Hj9LjMVex9NqcQnDRhIVglj",
      "originalText": "How many shares are eligible to sell during the Tender Offer?<br>You can find the number of eligible shares to sell in the Transaction overview. Note that this number (see screenshot) in the Transaction Overview page is the total number of shares that you are eligible to sell across all your holdings.<br><img height=\"260\" src=\"carta/public/13/images/5919393131023195261_KX3JTP50nq_xZd2ZamFmu5A8g6vEuI96V4m_-Tpe5KZSi-A1vDlhGNzxxNvujkqr5sbfTjj94tZDHWtg_WvpklWrYHKOQvEbmu5qwMJWS5-XAL5S7Hj9LjMVex9NqcQnDRhIVglj\" width=\"526\">",
      "associatedImage": {
        "url": "carta/public/13/images/5919393131023195261_KX3JTP50nq_xZd2ZamFmu5A8g6vEuI96V4m_-Tpe5KZSi-A1vDlhGNzxxNvujkqr5sbfTjj94tZDHWtg_WvpklWrYHKOQvEbmu5qwMJWS5-XAL5S7Hj9LjMVex9NqcQnDRhIVglj"
      }
    },
    "signals": [{
      "key": "FontBolded",
      "valueB": true
    }]
  }, {
    "id": "7243727723114301118",
    "text": {
      "text": "Each eligible option grant or certificate is allowed to sell up to the max eligible total (the cap), unless the option grant or the certificate has vested shares less than the cap. In this case, you can sell up to total shares vested per the option grant or certificate. However, you will not be able to request to sell more shares than the cap across your holdings.  For example, the max eligible total (the cap) here is 3000 shares. CS-44 is allowed to sell up to the cap 3000 shares, and ES-236 is also allowed to sell up to the cap 3000 shares. But the total shares requested to be sold cannot exceed 3000 shares. carta/public/13/images/6715742228562027004_I4OYqAS5x_qZGIu-R9AOfeYSBn45H--dP2u8vHuXP6tsWiohzGfOtt-8jg72PboFtqvoal7mzDAxGRTW8c_4OjIZdIfHTHO3lg_vapUJnk3zVNaQ6aGwFCrMEgzQCJB6RULqt_EJ  If the total shares requested to sell exceed the max eligible total (the cap), you will be prompted with an error to prevent you from moving forward. carta/public/13/images/1030308294520191419_ljQY84MiP8Q5ufeHY8hol6aexSYxDFnq5cBX1qUGFrsxH0OCwSngRjVcg0Vi61BvOkwZz90ul2_OWgxYKyLRU1fSG4dz_nG1nmwDpEokClMFxSSTJdxmjnJ5kGfv6-ThgDcds3Hf",
