        }
      }, {
        "text": "After reviewing the exercise details, one of two actions can be selected: Approve or Reject.If the option exercise approver selectsApprove this exercise request and sign, the bank transaction will begin. carta/public/13/images/7828278372923453702_0Q6aM7pTMc2mT6v0nYGb_CPufJJlZdFqnizWYt8H3eamR4jE-GQP3qr8Wlcnaqdt6Iv5RFmcoc7V4FnAW9AF3dt3L94DXLQYsmaRIZJixZRMmkOHr61MOWOsYFAdeIBji2nTN-7NIf the option exercise approver selectsReject this exercise request, they will be prompted to select a reason from the list and electronically sign to proceed.  NOTE: The selected reason will be included in the email notice sent to the optionholder upon rejection of their exercise request. carta/public/13/images/8258092827873995318_GpFXkBaz2OMQLqGYYkTWTf0IdnjEBDatwpN-ZQuHG6dwFA0AE_jo0lB5zkgd-XEy4HhvG2WmP1oKRiRUHDJXwcVCExSPqhPpNxE1esDwp0yB-T_NMYc5-MtD69a9Vu-xQShyHbW3",
        "originalText": "After reviewing the exercise details, one of two actions can be selected: Approve or Reject.  If the option exercise approver selects Approve this exercise request and sign, the bank transaction will begin.<br> <img height=\"84\" src=\"carta/public/13/images/7828278372923453702_0Q6aM7pTMc2mT6v0nYGb_CPufJJlZdFqnizWYt8H3eamR4jE-GQP3qr8Wlcnaqdt6Iv5RFmcoc7V4FnAW9AF3dt3L94DXLQYsmaRIZJixZRMmkOHr61MOWOsYFAdeIBji2nTN-7N\" width=\"482\"><br> &nbsp; If the option exercise approver selects Reject this exercise request, they will be prompted to select a reason from the list and electronically sign to proceed.<br> NOTE: The selected reason will be included in the email notice sent to the optionholder upon rejection of their exercise request.<br> <img height=\"223\" src=\"carta/public/13/images/8258092827873995318_GpFXkBaz2OMQLqGYYkTWTf0IdnjEBDatwpN-ZQuHG6dwFA0AE_jo0lB5zkgd-XEy4HhvG2WmP1oKRiRUHDJXwcVCExSPqhPpNxE1esDwp0yB-T_NMYc5-MtD69a9Vu-xQShyHbW3\" width=\"482\"><br> &nbsp;  ",
        "associatedImage": {
          "url": "carta/public/13/images/8258092827873995318_GpFXkBaz2OMQLqGYYkTWTf0IdnjEBDatwpN-ZQuHG6dwFA0AE_jo0lB5zkgd-XEy4HhvG2WmP1oKRiRUHDJXwcVCExSPqhPpNxE1esDwp0yB-T_NMYc5-MtD69a9Vu-xQShyHbW3"
        }
      }, {
        "text": "The approval modal will be different due to the tax obligations for ISO and NSO exercises.For an ISO exercise: There will be no tax withholding at the time of exercise to review.For NSO exercises: Tax withholdings can be manually updated during the approval step. Adjust the dollar amount by going on the right and selectReview exercise request.  NOTE: If there is no gain(FMV as of exercise date - option grant exercise price = 0) on the exercise date, NSO tax withholding will not occur. The amount shown is the maximum amount allowed by the federal and state laws. The amount can be adjusted lower according to the option holder's liability as needed. It is recommended to review the Tax rules set prior to allowing holders to exercise.  In addition, the withholding amount is not remitted to the IRS by Carta. The issuing company is responsible for remitting the taxes to IRS as the total exercise cost, plus any taxes collected, are sent in full to the company. If you are unfamiliar with remitting tax withholdings to the IRS, you should consult a tax professional or your payroll provider. carta/public/13/images/435014320530513335_fSD6Mg4OoiskLkZ7nuFdie2wz-bMeZxfPHxWtHH8WR9TW0MrRA6vRYM3lqcc_yjaHvjrlL4SBcwDHxZ4P9vafm6--SG84IV01KxscNygAwf0OrOTk3sGqIal-5irEP4XUOOPsau4For ISO/NSO split exercises, the option exercise approver will need to approve both portions separately via theExercises ledger for which the grant type will be clearly labeled.  NOTE: The exercise cannot be partially approved or rejected, as both ISO and NSO portions must be approved before proceeding.",
        "originalText": "The approval modal will be different due to the tax obligations for ISO and NSO exercises.  For an ISO exercise: There will be no tax withholding at the time of exercise to review.<br> &nbsp; For NSO exercises: Tax withholdings can be manually updated during the approval step. Adjust the dollar amount by going on the right and select Review exercise request.<br> NOTE: If there is no gain (FMV as of exercise date - option grant exercise price = 0) on the exercise date, NSO tax withholding will not occur. The amount shown is the maximum amount allowed by the federal and state laws. The amount can be adjusted lower according to the option holder's liability as needed. It is recommended to review the <a href=\"https://support.carta.com/s/article/manage-tax-withholding\" style=\"text-decoration: none;\" target=\"_blank\"><u>Tax rules</u></a> set prior to allowing holders to exercise.<br> In addition, the withholding amount is not remitted to the IRS by Carta. The issuing company is responsible for remitting the taxes to IRS as the total exercise cost, plus any taxes collected, are sent in full to the company. If you are unfamiliar with remitting tax withholdings to the IRS, you should consult a tax professional or your payroll provider.<br> <img height=\"415\" src=\"carta/public/13/images/435014320530513335_fSD6Mg4OoiskLkZ7nuFdie2wz-bMeZxfPHxWtHH8WR9TW0MrRA6vRYM3lqcc_yjaHvjrlL4SBcwDHxZ4P9vafm6--SG84IV01KxscNygAwf0OrOTk3sGqIal-5irEP4XUOOPsau4\" width=\"487\"><br> &nbsp; For ISO/NSO split exercises, the option exercise approver will need to approve both portions separately via the Exercises ledger for which the grant type will be clearly labeled.<br> NOTE: The exercise cannot be partially approved or rejected, as both ISO and NSO portions must be approved before proceeding.<br> &nbsp;  ",
        "associatedImage": {
