  "linked": [{
    "id": "-7776394326928561275",
    "text": {
      "text": "Flat file integrations pull data from an automatically uploaded spreadsheet containing customer data. This spreadsheet needs to be provided to Carta in an automated manner by the client’s HRIS Provider. The spreadsheet is a report generated by the HRIS Provider, created in collaboration with the customer. It is recommended that once a day, this spreadsheet/report is generated and uploaded/pushed into Carta's SFTP folder by the HRIS Provider.  The setup process for this type of integration requires involvement from both Carta and the HRIS Provider. Typically, HRIS Providers may charge an additional cost for this type of service. Also, due to the collaboration required between three parties (customer, Carta, and HRIS Provider), the setup process tends to be lengthier, typically lasting weeks to months.  The key difference between flat file integrations and API integrations is that for flat file, data is pushed into Carta, whereas for API-based, Carta is pulling the data.  Flat file integrations are recommended for Enterprise companies with more complex use cases.  Flat file integrations will work for any HRIS Provider that supports automated report uploads.ADP,Workday, andUltiPro are known to support this, but this list is not exhaustive. Learn if your HR/Payroll Provider supports the Carta flat file integration by asking your HRIS Provider if they supportautomated uploads of HR reports into SFTP folders. Flat file integrations arenot supported by Carta's Total Comp tool.  Learn more about flat file integrations and how to set it up here.",
      "originalText": "Flat file integrations pull data from an automatically uploaded spreadsheet containing customer data. This spreadsheet needs to be provided to Carta in an automated manner by the client’s HRIS Provider. The spreadsheet is a report generated by the HRIS Provider, created in collaboration with the customer. It is recommended that once a day, this spreadsheet/report is generated and uploaded/pushed into Carta's SFTP folder by the HRIS Provider.<br><br>The setup process for this type of integration requires involvement from both Carta and the HRIS Provider. Typically, HRIS Providers may charge an additional cost for this type of service. Also, due to the collaboration required between three parties (customer, Carta, and HRIS Provider), the setup process tends to be lengthier, typically lasting weeks to months.<br><br>The key difference between flat file integrations and API integrations is that for flat file, data is pushed into Carta, whereas for API-based, Carta is pulling the data.<br><br>Flat file integrations are recommended for Enterprise companies with more complex use cases.<br><br>Flat file integrations will work for any HRIS Provider that supports automated report uploads. ADP, Workday,&nbsp;and UltiPro are known to support this, but this list is not exhaustive. Learn if your HR/Payroll Provider supports the Carta flat file integration by asking your HRIS Provider if they support automated uploads of HR reports into SFTP folders. Flat file integrations are&nbsp;not&nbsp;supported by Carta's Total Comp tool.<br><br><a href=\"https://support.carta.com/s/article/flat-file-hris-integrations\" target=\"_blank\">Learn more about flat file integrations and how to set it up here</a>."
    }
  }]
}

