      }, {
        "text": "We follow the Portfolio Companies application of Depreciations and Amortization (“D&A”) when reporting Total Operating Expenses:We include them if the Portfolio Company has included it.We exclude them if the Portfolio Company has excluded it.If the client has not reported Total Operating Expenses, we include D&A as part of our calculations of total operating expenses.",
        "originalText": "We follow the Portfolio Companies application of Depreciations and Amortization (“D&amp;A”) when reporting Total Operating Expenses:  We include them if the Portfolio Company has included it. We exclude them if the Portfolio Company has excluded it. If the client has not reported Total Operating Expenses, we include D&amp;A as part of our calculations of total operating expenses.  "
      }, {
        "text": "If EBITDA is not included but Earnings or Net Income is included, we arrive at EBITDA by taking the Net Income or Earnings as provided, and adding (1) Interest, (2) Taxes, (3) Depreciation, and (4) Amortization (as provided) and will add them to Earnings or Net Income to arrive at EBITDA. If any of the above 4 are not included, we assume them to be 0 and will arrive and report EBITDA regardless. Note that in the absence of all four of these figures, EBITDA = Earnings or Net Income.Additionally, similarly named figures (Adjusted EBITDA, et al) will be considered as EBITDA when provided.",
        "originalText": "If EBITDA is not included but&nbsp;Earnings or Net Income is included, we arrive at EBITDA by taking the Net Income or Earnings as provided, and adding (1) Interest, (2) Taxes, (3) Depreciation, and (4) Amortization (as provided) and will add them to Earnings or Net Income to arrive at EBITDA. If any of the above 4 are not included, we assume them to be 0 and will arrive and report EBITDA regardless. Note that in the absence of all four of these figures, EBITDA = Earnings or Net Income.  Additionally, similarly named figures (Adjusted EBITDA, et al) will be considered as EBITDA when provided.  "
      }, {
        "text": "If Earnings or Net Income is not provided, we calculate it as Gross Profit less all reported expenses.",
        "originalText": "If Earnings or Net Income is not provided, we calculate it as Gross Profit less all reported expenses."
      }, {
        "text": "We use the terms Earnings, Comprehensive Income, or Net Income interchangeably and to mean Net Income (in the absence of each other). Otherwise, we will take the line item furthest down on the income statement as Net Income.",
        "originalText": "We use the terms Earnings, Comprehensive Income, or Net Income interchangeably and to mean Net Income (in the absence of each other). Otherwise, we will take the line item furthest down on the income statement as Net Income."
      }, {
        "text": "When possible, if the income statement is provided as year-to-date (“YTD”), we subtract the prior quarters (if they have been provided in prior quarters) and report the net-quarterly figure for the most recent figure provided.",
        "originalText": "When possible, if the income statement is provided as year-to-date (“YTD”), we subtract the prior quarters (if they have been provided in prior quarters) and report the net-quarterly figure for the most recent figure provided."
      }, {
        "text": "When possible, we take the most recently reported figure and override the prior reported figures.",
        "originalText": "When possible, we take the most recently reported figure and override the prior reported figures."
      }, {
        "text": "We do not report any changes or restatements to the financial figures (although historical figures and the dates which the historical figures have been reported) will remain available to download and analyze by the firm.",
        "originalText": "We do not report any changes or restatements to the financial figures (although historical figures and the dates which the historical figures have been reported) will remain available to download and analyze by the firm."
      }, {
        "text": "Unless previously scoped out with the firm, when we are provided annual forecasts, won’t break this out into quarters and thus it will not be reported.",
        "originalText": "Unless previously scoped out with the firm, when we are provided annual forecasts, won’t break this out into quarters and thus it will not be reported."
      }]
    }
  }]
