    }
  },
  "linked": [{
    "id": "-6135721058405380955",
    "text": {
      "text": "A transfer of shares is a secondary transaction where shares are transferred from one stakeholder to another. Ensure that you have all the transfer details ready when reflecting on Carta, but contact Carta Support if a reversal is needed.  For one-off transfers, you can reflect transfers in Carta two different ways:",
      "originalText": "A transfer of shares is a secondary transaction where shares are transferred from one stakeholder to another. Ensure that you have all the transfer details ready when reflecting on Carta, but&nbsp;<a href=\"https://support.carta.com/s/article/carta-help-center\" target=\"_blank\"><u>contact Carta Support</u></a> if a reversal is needed.<br><br>For one-off transfers, you can reflect transfers in Carta two different ways:"
    }
  }, {
    "id": "6053827082298691459",
    "list": {
      "isOrdered": true,
      "item": [{
        "text": "Full transfer: Transfer the full amount of certificate to one or multiple stakeholders. The original certificate will be marked as transferred, and the new certificates will be issued.",
        "originalText": "Full transfer: Transfer the full amount of certificate to one or multiple stakeholders. The original certificate will be marked as transferred, and the new certificates will be issued."
      }, {
        "text": "Partial transfer: Transfer a portion of a certificate to one or multiple stakeholders. The original certificate will be marked as transferred, and the balance of the untransferred shares will be reissued to the original stakeholder as a new certificate.",
        "originalText": "Partial transfer: Transfer a portion of a certificate to one or multiple stakeholders. The original certificate will be marked as transferred, and the balance of the untransferred shares will be reissued to the original stakeholder as a new certificate."
      }]
    }
  }, {
    "id": "1804329746607703038",
    "text": {
      "text": "If your company is going through a tender offer or secondary with a third party buyer, you can complete this process through the Carta feature. Find more information about setting up a secondary",
      "originalText": "If your company is going through a tender offer or secondary with a third party buyer, you can complete this process through the Carta feature. Find more information about setting up a secondary "
    }
  }, {
    "id": "7375028667183341536",
    "text": {
      "text": "here",
      "originalText": "<a href=\"https://support.carta.com/s/article/tender-offer-faq\" style=\"text-decoration: none;\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>"
    }
  }, {
    "id": "-3492872424732523793",
    "text": {
      "text": "If a transfer is needed due to a life event, such as a transfer to a Trust or due to a death, consult with your legal counsel prior to reflecting the transfer on Carta to ensure the proper legal documentation is executed.",
      "originalText": "If a transfer is needed due to a life event, such as a transfer to a Trust or due to a death, consult with your legal counsel prior to reflecting the transfer on Carta to ensure the proper legal documentation is executed. "
    }
  }, {
    "id": "4709722463973986372",
    "text": {
      "text": "For each transfer, the stakeholders must already exist in Carta.",
      "originalText": "For each transfer, the stakeholders must already exist in Carta. "
    }
  }, {
    "id": "-7850879030566794771",
    "text": {
      "text": "Learn more about adding stakeholders",
      "originalText": "<a href=\"https://support.carta.com/s/article/stakeholder-ledger\" style=\"text-decoration: none;\" target=\"_blank\">Learn more about adding stakeholders</a>"
    }
  }, {
    "id": "-5800275537086356477",
    "text": {
      "text": "Additionally, certificates can only be transferred from one to one or one to many. Multiple certificates cannot be transferred into one. If this is needed, the certificates must be canceled and reissued as one.",
      "originalText": "Additionally, certificates can only be transferred from one to one or one to many. Multiple certificates cannot be transferred into one. If this is needed, the certificates must be canceled and reissued as one. "
    }
  }, {
    "id": "-2881773129571024022",
    "text": {
      "text": "In this video demo, you will review how to transfer shares on Carta.",
      "originalText": "In this video demo, you will review how to transfer shares on Carta. "
    }
  }, {
