        }
      }, {
        "text": "A modal will then pop-up on the screen, prompting you to select which assumption you would like to change. Upload a custom term, interest rate, volatility, fair value (or option value as calculated offline in your own Black-Scholes calculator), the amortization method, or the expense status (where you can choose to include or exclude any awards).  carta/public/13/images/8400508865945150714_at2F86jh-91WjFT-X8kk5tjORy4lSqarPsQsZDji3-fZEsdsekH7-KSF0J4N_XjjQNNzSQ2hbE7pL6uqFOw7OQSxfKkoWUpa06Im8y4yVvDQOEm0OQT6cyLzNf-hDDJ2M5H1kT8X    NOTE: if you are attempting to edit the custom expected term, Carta will need you to also upload a custom interest rate and volatility as our calculation for these inputs are based on the Simplified Method to determine expected term.",
