{
  "id": "-6141848163312480215",
  "subject": {
    "id": "-6141848163312480215",
    "text": {
      "text": "Q. Why do I have \"N/A\" listed in my Cost Center tab?",
      "originalText": "<br>Q. Why do I have \"N/A\" listed in my Cost Center tab?"
    },
    "signals": [{
      "key": "FontBolded",
      "valueB": true
    }]
  },
  "linked": [{
    "id": "-3761694403957961722",
    "text": {
      "text": "A. As referenced in the previous question, if you enter in an effective date that does not line up with the vesting schedule, then the unapplied tranches will have a cost center of \"N/A\". In order to diagnose the issue and find out which tranches you'll want to fix, navigate to the \"Month-Year|Month-Year\" tab. From here, navigate to the \"Cost Center\" column at the far right and filter for all of the \"N/A\"'s. carta/public/13/images/1447241344253429877_rtaImage",
