{
  "id": "118544809961596880",
  "subject": {
    "id": "118544809961596880",
    "text": {
      "text": "WHAT IS EXPECTED TERM?",
      "originalText": "WHAT IS EXPECTED TERM?"
    },
    "signals": [{
      "key": "FontBolded",
      "valueB": true
    }]
  },
  "linked": [{
    "id": "1750925742592057238",
    "text": {
      "text": "The Expected Term of an option grant is the length of time the grant is expected to be outstanding before it is exercised or terminated. Since most employees who hold private market stock options tend to exercise their options before they expire due to termination or potential liquidity events, the expected life is shorter than the actual contractual term of the grant.",
      "originalText": "The&nbsp;Expected Term&nbsp;of an option grant is the length of time the grant is expected to be outstanding before it is exercised or terminated. Since most employees who hold private market stock options tend to exercise their options before they expire due to termination or potential liquidity events, the expected life is shorter than the actual contractual term of the grant."
    }
  }, {
    "id": "1942024288532663893",
    "text": {
      "text": "The expected term of a grant is one of the main assumptions used in the Black-Scholes fair value calculation. Many variables can affect the expected term or the expected life of the option grant, including but not limited to:",
      "originalText": "The expected term of a grant is one of the main assumptions used in the Black-Scholes fair value calculation. Many variables can affect the expected term or the expected life of the option grant, including but not limited to:"
    }
  }, {
    "id": "3140914029128680411",
    "list": {
      "item": [{
        "text": "Historical exercise patterns",
        "originalText": "Historical exercise patterns"
      }, {
        "text": "Employee demographics",
        "originalText": "Employee demographics"
      }, {
        "text": "Termination rates",
        "originalText": "Termination rates"
      }, {
        "text": "Expected volatility of the underlying stock",
        "originalText": "Expected volatility of the underlying stock"
      }, {
        "text": "Price of the underlying stock",
        "originalText": "Price of the underlying stock"
      }]
    }
  }, {
    "id": "5079809602008491428",
    "text": {
      "text": "However, as a private entity, some of these variables may be difficult, if not impossible, to reasonably determine due to the scarcity of data available. The SEC responded to this with a “practical expedient” or proposed solution for option grants deemed to be “plain-vanilla” known widely as the Simplified Method or mid-point method, which is described in the Staff Accounting Bulletin 107 (SAB 107) found here.",
      "originalText": "However, as a private entity, some of these variables may be difficult, if not impossible, to reasonably determine due to the scarcity of data available. The SEC responded to this with a “practical expedient” or proposed solution for option grants deemed to be “plain-vanilla” known widely as the Simplified Method or mid-point method, which is described in the Staff Accounting Bulletin 107 (SAB 107) found&nbsp;<a href=\"https://www.sec.gov/interps/account/sab107.pdf\" target=\"_blank\">here</a>."
    }
  }, {
    "id": "5768590339305582515",
    "text": {
      "text": "CALCULATING EXPECTED TERM",
      "originalText": "<br>CALCULATING EXPECTED TERM"
    },
    "signals": [{
      "key": "FontBolded",
      "valueB": true
    }]
  }, {
    "id": "-2622024149585958193",
    "text": {
      "text": "Carta follows the same methodology as described in SAB 107 for all employee option grants. This calculation is applied to each grant. SAB 107 describes the use of a simplified method for plain vanilla options with insufficient exercise history. The simplified method’s formula is:",
      "originalText": "Carta follows the same methodology as described in SAB 107 for all employee option grants. This calculation is applied to each grant. SAB 107 describes the use of a simplified method for plain vanilla options with insufficient exercise history. The simplified method’s formula is:"
    }
  }, {
    "id": "-3234039410298813202",
    "text": {
      "text": "carta/public/13/images/8758548785733660369_rtaImage",
      "originalText": "<img alt=\"\" src=\"carta/public/13/images/8758548785733660369_rtaImage\">",
      "associatedImage": {
        "url": "carta/public/13/images/8758548785733660369_rtaImage"
      }
    }
  }, {
    "id": "-4213727572051015076",
    "text": {
      "text": "Here is a snippet from a sample excel spreadsheet to follow along:",
      "originalText": "<br>Here is a snippet from a sample excel spreadsheet to follow along:"
    }
  }, {
    "id": "4132898666227251991",
    "text": {
      "text": "carta/public/13/images/1253466697396106387_rtaImage",
      "originalText": "<img alt=\"\" src=\"carta/public/13/images/1253466697396106387_rtaImage\">",
      "associatedImage": {
        "url": "carta/public/13/images/1253466697396106387_rtaImage"
      }
    }
  }, {
    "id": "-353203487709929456",
    "text": {
      "text": "The first step is to determine the weighted average remaining time to vesting for each tranche. Carta does this by using the following equation:",
      "originalText": "<br>The first step is to determine the weighted average remaining time to vesting for each tranche. Carta does this by using the following equation:&nbsp;"
    }
  }, {
    "id": "-9181268515628987468",
    "text": {
      "text": "carta/public/13/images/8011256972331042664_rtaImage",
      "originalText": "<img alt=\"\" src=\"carta/public/13/images/8011256972331042664_rtaImage\">",
      "associatedImage": {
        "url": "carta/public/13/images/8011256972331042664_rtaImage"
      }
    }
  }, {
    "id": "7196257224054975595",
    "text": {
      "text": "The Weighted Average Time to Vest is then divided by the number of shares granted to arrive at the Weighted Average Vesting Term.",
      "originalText": "<br>The Weighted Average Time to Vest is then divided by the number of shares granted to arrive at the Weighted Average Vesting Term."
    }
  }, {
    "id": "-7712573610996756869",
    "text": {
      "text": "The next step is to determine the Contractual Term, which is simply defined by the following equation",
      "originalText": "<br>The next step is to determine the Contractual Term, which is simply defined by the following equation"
    }
  }, {
    "id": "2955958574085500105",
    "text": {
      "text": "carta/public/13/images/7665363825357747975_rtaImage",
      "originalText": "<img alt=\"\" src=\"carta/public/13/images/7665363825357747975_rtaImage\">",
      "associatedImage": {
        "url": "carta/public/13/images/7665363825357747975_rtaImage"
      }
    }
  }, {
    "id": "5182138125507440568",
    "text": {
      "text": "The commonly accepted way of defining contractual term is simply the expiration date minus the grant date, divided by the number of days in the year. Some entities prefer to use 360 or 365 day-count, but Carta uses 365.25 days to account for Leap years.",
      "originalText": "<br>The commonly accepted way of defining contractual term is simply the expiration date minus the grant date, divided by the number of days in the year. Some entities prefer to use 360 or 365 day-count, but Carta uses 365.25 days to account for Leap years."
    }
  }, {
    "id": "6797300676532320035",
    "text": {
      "text": "Once you have both the Vesting Term and the Contractual Term, simply sum the Weighted Average Vesting Term and the Contractual Term and divide by 2.",
      "originalText": "<br>Once you have both the Vesting Term and the Contractual Term, simply sum the Weighted Average Vesting Term and the Contractual Term and divide by 2."
    }
  }, {
    "id": "7795437562541494828",
    "text": {
      "text": "EXPECTED TERM CALCULATION FOR NON-EMPLOYEES",
      "originalText": "<br>EXPECTED TERM CALCULATION FOR NON-EMPLOYEES"
    },
    "signals": [{
      "key": "FontBolded",
      "valueB": true
    }]
  }, {
    "id": "2859835718200615644",
    "text": {
      "text": "Non-employees use a remaining contractual life to measure the remaining life of an award. The remaining contractual life is defined by the following equation:",
      "originalText": "Non-employees use a remaining contractual life to measure the remaining life of an award. The remaining contractual life is defined by the following equation:"
    }
  }, {
    "id": "-4008574951861774728",
    "text": {
      "text": "carta/public/13/images/8485662072397357805_rtaImage",
      "originalText": "<img alt=\"\" src=\"carta/public/13/images/8485662072397357805_rtaImage\">",
      "associatedImage": {
        "url": "carta/public/13/images/8485662072397357805_rtaImage"
      }
    }
  }, {
    "id": "-8353331976246466578",
    "text": {
      "text": "Prior to adoption of ASU 2018-07, companies are required to re-measure non-employee option grants until they vest under ASC505-50. To comply, the expected term of non-employee option grants is re-measured each reporting period until the award vests. For a grant whose vest date is before the reporting period end date, the expected term will be the grant expiration date less the vest date. For grants whose vest date is after the reporting period end date, the expected term will be the expiration date less the reporting period end date.",
      "originalText": "<br>Prior to adoption of ASU 2018-07, companies are required to re-measure non-employee option grants until they vest under ASC505-50. To comply, the expected term of non-employee option grants is re-measured each reporting period until the award vests. For a grant whose vest date is before the reporting period end date, the expected term will be the grant expiration date less the vest date. For grants whose vest date is after the reporting period end date, the expected term will be the expiration date less the reporting period end date.&nbsp;"
    }
  }, {
    "id": "3749655893494996477",
    "text": {
      "text": "carta/public/13/images/2564650681472520398_rtaImage",
      "originalText": "<img alt=\"\" src=\"carta/public/13/images/2564650681472520398_rtaImage\">",
      "associatedImage": {
        "url": "carta/public/13/images/2564650681472520398_rtaImage"
      }
    }
  }, {
    "id": "4703659264220485356",
    "text": {
      "text": "Once both dates have been established, take the difference of the two and divide it by 365.25 to arrive at the remaining contractual life of a grant.",
      "originalText": "<br>Once both dates have been established, take the difference of the two and divide it by 365.25 to arrive at the remaining contractual life of a grant.&nbsp;"
    }
  }, {
    "id": "-227055774628226606",
    "text": {
      "text": "carta/public/13/images/2256432534449163496_rtaImage",
      "originalText": "<img alt=\"\" src=\"carta/public/13/images/2256432534449163496_rtaImage\">",
      "associatedImage": {
        "url": "carta/public/13/images/2256432534449163496_rtaImage"
      }
    }
  }]
}

{
  "id": "5275227390346479315",
  "subject": {
    "id": "5275227390346479315",
    "text": {
      "text": "Repricing Procedure:",
      "originalText": "<br>Repricing Procedure:"
    },
    "signals": [{
      "valueL": "3"
    }]
  },
  "linked": [{
    "id": "9100287687837328744",
    "list": {
      "isOrdered": true,
      "item": [{
        "text": "Navigate to Securities > Equity Awards and click Manage equity plans > Request repricing.  carta/public/13/images/3452560843998356848_rtaImage",
        "originalText": "Navigate to Securities &gt; Equity Awards and click Manage equity plans &gt; Request&nbsp;&nbsp;repricing.<br> <img alt=\"\" src=\"carta/public/13/images/3452560843998356848_rtaImage\">",
        "associatedImage": {
          "url": "carta/public/13/images/3452560843998356848_rtaImage"
        }
      }, {
        "text": "Enter in the effective date and new exercise price. Click Next: review repricing request.  carta/public/13/images/6231722641691703063_rtaImage",
        "originalText": "Enter in the effective date and new exercise price. Click&nbsp;Next: review repricing request.<br> <img alt=\"\" src=\"carta/public/13/images/6231722641691703063_rtaImage\">",
        "associatedImage": {
          "url": "carta/public/13/images/6231722641691703063_rtaImage"
        }
      }, {
        "text": "After reviewing the request, click Request repricing to send the request to the Carta support team. They will reach out to you via email within 3 business days to send modeled reports, discuss changes, and execute the repricing.  carta/public/13/images/7981628389517026835_rtaImage",
        "originalText": "After reviewing the request, click Request repricing to send the request to the Carta support team. They will reach out to you via email within 3 business days to send modeled reports, discuss changes, and execute the repricing.<br> <img alt=\"\" src=\"carta/public/13/images/7981628389517026835_rtaImage\">",
        "associatedImage": {
          "url": "carta/public/13/images/7981628389517026835_rtaImage"
        }
      }, {
        "text": "All repriced options have been logged in Carta and you are now ready to generate the report to include the repriced options!  Navigate to Compliance > Expense Accounting.  carta/public/13/images/3932714533911969815_rtaImage",
        "originalText": "All repriced options have been logged in Carta and you are now ready to generate the report to include the repriced options!<br> Navigate to Compliance &gt; Expense Accounting.<br> <img alt=\"\" src=\"carta/public/13/images/3932714533911969815_rtaImage\">",
        "associatedImage": {
          "url": "carta/public/13/images/3932714533911969815_rtaImage"
        }
      }, {
        "text": "Run the report by selecting Create a new report.  carta/public/13/images/7005854663111042957_rtaImage",
        "originalText": "Run the report by selecting Create a new report.<br> <img alt=\"\" src=\"carta/public/13/images/7005854663111042957_rtaImage\">",
        "associatedImage": {
          "url": "carta/public/13/images/7005854663111042957_rtaImage"
        }
      }, {
        "text": "Once the reports are done generating, you will now see three reports listed in the drop-down menu: the grant-date report, the mark-to-market report, and the incremental report.    The incremental report will take the original grant with the underwater exercise price and value it on the date of the repricing. It will then look at the new version of the grant with the new exercise price and value it on the day of the repricing as well. The incremental expense will then be the difference between the fair value of the new grant and the original grant. You will need to add the incremental expense shown on the Expense Summary tab to the grant-date and mark-to-market expense to find the total amount recognized during the current reporting period.",
        "originalText": "Once the reports are done generating, you will now see three reports listed in the drop-down menu: the grant-date report, the mark-to-market report, and the incremental report.<br> <br> The incremental report will take the original grant with the underwater exercise price and value it on the date of the repricing. It will then look at the new version of the grant with the new exercise price and value it on the day of the repricing as well. The incremental expense will then be the difference between the fair value of the new grant and the original grant. You will need to add the incremental expense shown on the Expense Summary tab to the grant-date and mark-to-market expense to find the total amount recognized during the current reporting period."
      }]
    }
  }]
}

{
  "id": "-8023167504537100155",
