    "text": {
      "text": "On a quarterly and annual basis, borrowers must certify that they are in compliance with all required covenants in the LSA by submitting a compliance certificate.  SelectingSubmit compliance certificate on theLine of Credit Summary orAccount Summary page will access the form to submit a certificate. The borrower must select the appropriate reporting period and answer all required questions. If the borrower needs to submit supplementary documents separately, email them to loanops@carta.com.  An Operator can complete the certificate (screenshot shown below) and submit to the Signer for signature. A Signer can either sign these submitted forms or fill one out, sign, and submit directly. Both an Operator and a Signer can retract unsigned compliance certificates (e.g. certificate was filled out in error or is no longer applicable). carta/public/13/images/3531393071501492700_znj-7ly-njpE9JHJc9W3jx9LwgsDI88SJ1uf9HaTYK_wluu83FUplpvxt7zdHOD-pRRyGuJuE798ssYtiqpQqjvCfYdkwCjHSWXGwz0F2azUtTxG_CLDCT4jfXodiIumLjGuJBGB",
