{
  "id": "2032766386566000778",
  "subject": {
    "id": "2032766386566000778",
    "text": {
      "text": "What is the Asset Approach? Why was the Asset Approach used as the 409A valuation methodology?"
    }
  },
  "linked": [{
    "id": "-19005227670814802",
    "text": {
      "text": "The Asset Approach is utilized when the company is pre-revenue (or has minimal revenue), and has not raised a priced equity round of financing as of the Valuation Date. The Asset Approach is also utilized if the company has raised a priced equity round of financing but experienced a material pivot following the financing, or if the priced equity round of financing was determined to be non- arm's length. This methodology is used for very early-stage companies that do not have material revenue, positive EBITDA, or a market indication of value.  The Asset Approach is based on the cost-to-recreate worksheet, which is submitted by your management team. The worksheet attempts to capture the costs a third-party would incur to recreate the company's assets from inception through the Valuation Date. Inception can be defined as when you/your employees and/or contractors began to devote significant time into the current business venture.  There are two components to the worksheet, including personnel costs and fixed costs.",
      "originalText": "The Asset Approach is utilized when the company is pre-revenue (or has minimal revenue), and has not raised a priced equity round of financing as of the Valuation Date. The Asset Approach is also utilized if the company has raised a priced equity round of financing but experienced a material pivot following the financing, or if the priced equity round of financing was determined to be non-<a href=\"https://support.carta.com/s/article/arm-length-transaction-backsolve\" target=\"_blank\"><u>arm's length</u></a>. This methodology is used for very early-stage companies that do not have material revenue, positive EBITDA, or a market indication of value.&nbsp;<br><br>The Asset Approach is based on the cost-to-recreate worksheet, which is submitted by your management team. The worksheet attempts to capture the costs a third-party would incur to recreate the company's assets from inception through the Valuation Date. Inception can be defined as when you/your employees and/or contractors began to devote significant time into the current business venture.<br><br>There are two components to the worksheet, including personnel costs and fixed costs."
    }
  }, {
    "id": "-6446892727843178156",
    "list": {
      "isOrdered": true,
      "item": [{
        "text": "Personnel costs include market-rate monthly pay, and the total number of months that each employee and/or contractor was employed since the company’s inception.",
        "originalText": "Personnel costs include market-rate monthly pay, and the total number of months that each employee and/or contractor was employed since the company’s inception."
      }, {
        "text": "Fixed costs (referred to as \"overhead\") are non-personnel costs that have been incurred since the Company's inception, including rent, IT equipment, software, etc.",
        "originalText": "Fixed costs (referred to as \"overhead\") are non-personnel costs that have been incurred since the Company's inception, including rent, IT equipment, software, etc."
      }]
    }
  }, {
    "id": "-4306636239386882486",
    "text": {
      "text": "If you have indicated on the request form that your company has neither raised any priced rounds of equity, nor has generated more than $500,000 in revenue during the twelve months prior to the Valuation Date, then you will need to complete the cost-to-recreate worksheet. If you need assistance completing the cost-to-recreate worksheet, contact val-operations@carta.com.",
      "originalText": "<br>If you have indicated on the request form that your company has neither raised any priced rounds of equity, nor has generated more than $500,000 in revenue during the twelve months prior to the Valuation Date, then you will need to complete the cost-to-recreate worksheet. If you need assistance completing the cost-to-recreate worksheet, contact <a href=\"mailto:val-support@carta.com\" style=\"text-decoration: none;\" target=\"_blank\">val-operations@carta.com</a>."
    }
  }, {
    "id": "-7597657857036361184",
    "text": {
      "text": "Below is an example of the worksheet. carta/public/13/images/1687640512366804598_fGbC9x-lTZ9W0e9rU8RK8-h2BMvT-QxW00UPGLcGZTHz0nq0H67iCvZbGVQsSM0F-L33IU73TUcLqhBjwHZ0xxZeGiDKutLKtZ_VizI1mFgbw3wlO94q1G84YtO2IPTL_-wYN1Ds",
      "originalText": "Below is an example of the worksheet.<br><img height=\"487\" src=\"carta/public/13/images/1687640512366804598_fGbC9x-lTZ9W0e9rU8RK8-h2BMvT-QxW00UPGLcGZTHz0nq0H67iCvZbGVQsSM0F-L33IU73TUcLqhBjwHZ0xxZeGiDKutLKtZ_VizI1mFgbw3wlO94q1G84YtO2IPTL_-wYN1Ds\" style=\"margin-left: 0px;margin-top: 0px;\" width=\"624\">",
