    "id": "-6619492065590382041",
    "text": {
      "text": "Exhibit B displays the values at which different classes of equity participate in proceeds upon an exit event (as detailed by the “Description” column). In other words, the first row represents the liquidation preference being paid to Series Seed Preferred. Following, the second, third, and fourth rows represent the Company values at which different share classes participate in the exit proceeds: first common shares, then options with a strike of $0.25, and then Series Seed Preferred with a conversion price of $1.00.",
      "originalText": "Exhibit B displays the values at which different classes of equity participate in proceeds upon an exit event (as detailed by the “Description” column). In other words, the first row represents the liquidation preference being paid to Series Seed Preferred. Following, the second, third, and fourth rows represent the Company values at which different share classes participate in the exit proceeds: first common shares, then options with a strike of $0.25, and then Series Seed Preferred with a conversion price of $1.00."
