  }, {
    "id": "242815503485017620",
    "list": {
      "item": [{
        "text": "In the first row, if the Company exits between $0 and $5,000,000, all proceeds will go to the liquidation preference of Series Seed Preferred.",
        "originalText": "In the first row, if the Company exits between $0 and $5,000,000, all proceeds will go to the liquidation preference of Series Seed Preferred.<br> &nbsp;"
      }, {
        "text": "In the second row, if the Company exits for between $5,000,000 and $7,625,000, then all proceeds in excess of the Series Seed Preferred liquidation preference will be distributed to the common shares. For example, if the Company exits for $7,625,000, then $2,625,000 will be distributed to the common shares pro rata. The calculation of $2,625,000 is shown in the “Delta” column, and is simply the difference between the “From” and “To” columns. It is calculated by multiplying the outstanding common shares of 10,500,000 by the options strike price of $0.25.",
        "originalText": "In the second row, if the Company exits for between $5,000,000 and $7,625,000, then all proceeds in excess of the Series Seed Preferred liquidation preference will be distributed to the common shares. For example, if the Company exits for $7,625,000, then $2,625,000 will be distributed to the common shares pro rata. The calculation of $2,625,000 is shown in the “Delta” column, and is simply the difference between the “From” and “To” columns. It is calculated by multiplying the outstanding common shares of 10,500,000 by the options strike price of $0.25.<br> &nbsp;"
      }, {
        "text": "In the third row, if the Company exits for between $7,625,000 and $17,900,000, then proceeds in excess of $7,625,000 will be distributed to the common shares and the options (now common shares) pro rata. For example, if the Company exits for $17,900,000, $10,275,000 will be distributed to the common shares and the options. The figure $10,275,000 is calculated by multiplying the sum of outstanding common shares and options of 13,700,000 by $0.75. The distribution of $0.75 is calculated by taking the Series Seed Preferred’s conversion price of $1.00, and subtracting the amount previously distributed to the common shares of $0.25.",
        "originalText": "In the third row, if the Company exits for between $7,625,000 and $17,900,000, then proceeds in excess of $7,625,000 will be distributed to the common shares and the options (now common shares) pro rata. For example, if the Company exits for $17,900,000, $10,275,000 will be distributed to the common shares and the options. The figure $10,275,000 is calculated by multiplying the sum of outstanding common shares and options of 13,700,000 by $0.75. The distribution of $0.75 is calculated by taking the Series Seed Preferred’s conversion price of $1.00, and subtracting the amount previously distributed to the common shares of $0.25.&nbsp;<br> &nbsp;"
      }, {
        "text": "In the fourth row, if the Company exits for a value above $17,900,000, then all proceeds will be distributed to common shares, options (now common shares), and Series Seed Preferred shares (now common shares) pro rata.",
        "originalText": "In the fourth row, if the Company exits for a value above $17,900,000, then all proceeds will be distributed to common shares, options (now common shares), and Series Seed Preferred shares (now common shares) pro rata."
      }]
