    "id": "8688564352860480153",
    "text": {
      "text": "The “Incremental value” column represents the slice of option value for each breakpoint. In the first row, the incremental value equals the value of the Company (i.e., $10,000,000) minus the option value in that row (i.e. $6,802,094). In the following rows, the incremental value equals the difference between the option value in the prior row, and the option value in the current row. The sum of the incremental value column equals the value of the Company (i.e. $10,000,000).",
      "originalText": "The “Incremental value” column represents the slice of option value for each breakpoint. In the first row, the incremental value equals the value of the Company (i.e., $10,000,000) minus the option value in that row (i.e. $6,802,094). In the following rows, the incremental value equals the difference between the option value in the prior row, and the option value in the current row. The sum of the incremental value column equals the value of the Company (i.e. $10,000,000)."
