      "text": "The first key step in re-calculating volatility in the V2 Expense Details report is to accurately calculate continuous returns. This will be completed on the worksheet titledPeer data.  This worksheet contains closing prices for all peer ticker symbols, and looks like this: carta/public/13/images/4056441702954334188_SfOuPx2wPlGGD3l_lhh6TSScx1Uah4NeCT1J3xTbZHsaDa5kPmOhhIFa_HQTEa0S7iYVCeKfisSr3a-cEuVh3U_Xn1fYp8EFOLeBFR13Mu5HkU_1ajCdsMVPxCMmEP_FbTRVGS1P  Each ticker will need a column that will be used to calculate returns, which need to be added to the spreadsheet. An example of what the spreadsheet will look like after columns are added is highlighted below: carta/public/13/images/58227061720278753_bMiDB9BQRALdlGTLrS81_ldQcaEnK8yAjBTGlHLhCYSU5w9aynQDwe4o5L7V9mCszMpk-FPQiFul66MMSCB9byQ-Ikf2ETuDCAoMCbp62_dGBwvDwTr7KZqRTwMULW6QJTq8PMW-  Returns are calculated using the LN() function in excel. In its most basic form, the calculation looks like this: carta/public/13/images/4543981006039985354_H4nEucQDkkr-wRzzLSqIu0qtsLR9XAda-KYJKSYvZrkR4XAc8GojxJ8xeK5JTW_7SAniQHUoadwVd_z-1w0RhbG97tXMjrQPL6u-NfhpqYnS5gkhL_3LEwoFKxTi_5Pqf4Cb-W9f  This simple formula would work if there were never any days without trading data, however it is common for low trade volume ticker symbols to be frequently missing a daily trading price. Because of this, the formula that should be used gets more complex. Below is the suggested formula which will accurately calculate returns for data sets that have 4 or fewer consecutive days of no trading prices. Returns will not be calculated on days that do not have a trading price, and the embedded IFERROR() functions will move the denominator back if a prior day is missing trade data. If a data set has longer stretches of no trading data, manual formula adjustment is recommended. Note: The returns in row 5 will not need a formula to be entered; Always start on row 6 with the following:",
      "originalText": "The first key step in re-calculating volatility in the V2 Expense Details report is to accurately calculate continuous returns. This will be completed on the worksheet titled Peer data. &nbsp;<br><br>This worksheet contains closing prices for all peer ticker symbols, and looks like this:<br><img height=\"179\" src=\"carta/public/13/images/4056441702954334188_SfOuPx2wPlGGD3l_lhh6TSScx1Uah4NeCT1J3xTbZHsaDa5kPmOhhIFa_HQTEa0S7iYVCeKfisSr3a-cEuVh3U_Xn1fYp8EFOLeBFR13Mu5HkU_1ajCdsMVPxCMmEP_FbTRVGS1P\" style=\"margin-left: 0px;margin-top: 0px;\" width=\"624\"> &nbsp;<br><br>Each ticker will need a column that will be used to calculate returns, which need to be added to the spreadsheet. An example of what the spreadsheet will look like after columns are added is highlighted below:<br><img height=\"147\" src=\"carta/public/13/images/58227061720278753_bMiDB9BQRALdlGTLrS81_ldQcaEnK8yAjBTGlHLhCYSU5w9aynQDwe4o5L7V9mCszMpk-FPQiFul66MMSCB9byQ-Ikf2ETuDCAoMCbp62_dGBwvDwTr7KZqRTwMULW6QJTq8PMW-\" style=\"margin-left: 0px;margin-top: 0px;\" width=\"624\"> &nbsp;<br><br>Returns are calculated using the LN() function in excel. In its most basic form, the calculation looks like this:<br><img height=\"242\" src=\"carta/public/13/images/4543981006039985354_H4nEucQDkkr-wRzzLSqIu0qtsLR9XAda-KYJKSYvZrkR4XAc8GojxJ8xeK5JTW_7SAniQHUoadwVd_z-1w0RhbG97tXMjrQPL6u-NfhpqYnS5gkhL_3LEwoFKxTi_5Pqf4Cb-W9f\" style=\"margin-left: 0px;margin-top: 0px;\" width=\"500\"> &nbsp;<br><br>This simple formula would work if there were never any days without trading data, however it is common for low trade volume ticker symbols to be frequently missing a daily trading price. Because of this, the formula that should be used gets more complex. Below is the suggested formula which will accurately calculate returns for data sets that have 4 or fewer consecutive days of no trading prices. Returns will not be calculated on days that do not have a trading price, and the embedded IFERROR() functions will move the denominator back if a prior day is missing trade data. If a data set has longer stretches of no trading data, manual formula adjustment is recommended.<br>Note: The returns in row 5 will not need a formula to be entered; Always start on row 6 with the following:",
      "associatedImage": {
