      "text": "When an option holder terminates his or her service with a company, they are given a period of time to exercise their options (an \"exercise period\") before the allocated shares return to the option pool. If needed, exercise periods can also be updated on individual grants from theSecurity > Equity Awards page, shown here.  These periods help Legal Administrators auto-fill the exercise expiration date when they terminate a stakeholder, shown here, which can also be corrected or updated at a future time, as shown here.  The termination definitions below vary from plan to plan. If you are an option holder, refer to your plan documents for the termination definitions that apply to you. Not all plans specify every termination type below.",
