{
  "id": "-9086642561493678875",
  "subject": {
    "id": "-9086642561493678875",
    "text": {
      "text": "Enabling Online Transactions for US Companies"
    }
  },
  "linked": [{
    "id": "-7458084941658994751",
    "text": {
      "text": "All US companies can enable online transactions (ACH for US employees and wire for international employees) to allow money to be sent through Carta (hence, online) for option exercises, repurchases, and other transactions. To do this, administrators must configureTransaction Settings and add an ACH bank account. Once configured, online-wire for international exercises are available, meaning an international exercise will include wire instructions to send the money to Carta.  This simplifies the administrative workflow as it automatically records the receipt of funds and triggers subsequent steps of the transaction. Once enabled, shareholders will be able to submit requests and settle payment for their exercises on the Carta platform.  Once funds are received in full, they are deposited via ACH into the company’s preferred deposit bank account. Shares will then be issued to the shareholder and their certificates will appear in the company’s cap table. Learn more about the fund transfer workflow from US shareholders and non-US shareholders. If you do not currently have this view, review information about the legacy feature.",
      "originalText": "All US companies can enable online transactions (ACH for US employees and wire for international employees) to allow money to be sent through Carta (hence, online) for option exercises, repurchases, and other transactions. To do this, administrators must configure Transaction Settings and add an ACH bank account. Once configured, online-wire for international exercises are available, meaning an international exercise will include wire instructions to send the money to Carta.<br><br>This simplifies the administrative workflow as it automatically records the receipt of funds and triggers subsequent steps of the transaction. Once enabled, shareholders will be able to submit requests and settle payment for their exercises on the Carta platform.<br><br>Once funds are received in full, they are deposited via ACH into the company’s preferred deposit bank account. Shares will then be issued to the shareholder and their certificates will appear in the company’s cap table. Learn more about the fund transfer workflow from <a href=\"https://support.carta.com/s/article/fund-transfer-workflow\" target=\"_blank\"><u>US shareholders</u></a> and <a href=\"https://support.carta.com/s/article/non-us-fund-transfer-workflow\" target=\"_blank\"><u>non-US shareholders</u></a>.<br><br>&nbsp;<br>If you do not currently have this view,&nbsp; <a href=\"https://support.carta.com/s/article/online-transactions\" target=\"_blank\"><u>review information about the legacy feature</u></a>."
    }
  }, {
    "id": "-6799918755804576876",
    "text": {
      "text": "NOTE: The legacy setting is being deprecated and is functionally replaced by the new Transactions Settings. Upon setting up the Transaction Settings, this legacy online transactions toggle will disappear. It is important to update your transaction settings to support online wire transfers and to ensure there is no disruption in the future. For further assistance, contact Carta Support.",
      "originalText": "NOTE: The legacy setting is being deprecated and is functionally replaced by the new Transactions Settings. Upon setting up the Transaction Settings, this legacy online transactions toggle will disappear. It is important to update your transaction settings to support online wire transfers and to ensure there is no disruption in the future. For further assistance, contact <a href=\"https://support.carta.com/s/article/carta-help-center\" target=\"_blank\"><u>Carta Support</u></a>."
    }
  }, {
    "id": "5529927811111646386",
    "list": {
      "item": [{
        "text": "Enabling or Disabling Online Transactions"
      }]
    }
  }]
