{
  "id": "-9002737346684071670",
  "subject": {
    "id": "-9002737346684071670",
    "text": {
      "text": "Why is this date listed as the Date of Exercise on an ACH or Wire exercise?"
    }
  },
  "linked": [{
    "id": "-7069043341829736753",
    "text": {
      "text": "Exercising via ACH is available for US optionholders of US-based companies. For an ACH exercise, Carta records the effective date as the date the optionholder submits the request to exercise as the exercise date. At the time the optionholder submits the exercise request, they are irrevocably committing to complete and fund the exercise, similar to handing the completed option paperwork along with a paper check in person, as they agree to have the funds withdrawn from their connected bank account and transferred to Carta. Here are some related articles to the ACH exercise workflow:",
      "originalText": " Exercising via ACH is available for US optionholders of US-based companies. For an ACH exercise, Carta records the effective date as the date the optionholder submits the request to exercise as the exercise date. At the time the optionholder submits the exercise request, they are irrevocably committing to complete and fund the exercise, similar to handing the completed option paperwork along with a paper check in person, as they agree to have the funds withdrawn from their connected bank account and transferred to Carta. Here are some related articles to the ACH exercise workflow:&nbsp; "
    }
  }, {
    "id": "-5710713915044416764",
    "list": {
      "item": [{
        "text": "Exercising as an optionholder",
        "originalText": "<a href=\"https://support.carta.com/s/article/exercising-as-an-option-holder\" target=\"_blank\">Exercising as an optionholder</a>"
      }, {
        "text": "Viewing ACH exercise status",
        "originalText": "<a href=\"https://support.carta.com/s/article/view-ach-exercise-status\" target=\"_blank\">Viewing ACH exercise status</a>"
      }, {
        "text": "83(b) form for early exercised option grants",
        "originalText": "<a href=\"https://support.carta.com/s/article/form-83b-option-exercises\" target=\"_blank\">83(b) form for early exercised option grants</a>"
      }]
    }
  }, {
    "id": "2848838538439251286",
    "text": {
      "text": "Wire exercising is available for optionholders that do not qualify for ACH exercising. For Wire exercises, the exercise date will be the date that Carta receives the full exercise amount. Even though the exercise workflow is initiated and tracked on Carta, the funds transfer is dependent on the optionholder manually wiring funds for submission. The optionholder has 30 days from exercise approval for the funds to be received by Carta. If the funds are not received in this time, the exercise will be canceled or require resubmission. Here are some related articles to the wire exercise workflow:",
      "originalText": "Wire exercising is available for optionholders that do not qualify for ACH exercising. For Wire exercises, the exercise date will be the date that Carta receives the full exercise amount. Even though the exercise workflow is initiated and tracked on Carta, the funds transfer is dependent on the optionholder manually wiring funds for submission. The optionholder has 30 days from exercise approval for the &nbsp;funds to be received by Carta. If the funds are not received in this time, the exercise will be canceled or require resubmission.&nbsp;Here are some related articles to the wire exercise workflow:&nbsp; "
    }
  }, {
